<eesti>&sect; 1. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 1. </inglise>
<eesti>Seaduse reguleerimisala </eesti>
<inglise>Scope of application of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse reguleerimisala on vaba ettev&otilde;tluse huvidest l&auml;htuva konkurentsi kaitsmine loodusvarade kaevandamisel, toodete valmistamisel ja teenuste osutamisel ning toodete ja teenuste (edaspidi kaubad) ostmisel ja m&uuml;&uuml;misel ning muus &auml;ritegevuses konkurentsi takistamise, piiramise v&otilde;i kahjustamise (edaspidi kahjustamine) &auml;rahoidmine ja k&otilde;rvaldamine. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The scope of application of this Act is the safeguarding of competition in the interest of free enterprise upon the extraction of natural resources, manufacture of goods, provision of services and sale and purchase of products and services (hereinafter goods), and the preclusion and elimination of the prevention, limitation or restriction (hereinafter restriction) of competition in other economic activities. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esolevat seadust kohaldatakse ka juhul, kui konkurentsi kahjustamisele suunatud tegevus v&otilde;i tegevusetus toimub v&auml;ljaspool Eesti territooriumi, kuid kahjustab konkurentsi Eesti territooriumil. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) This Act also applies if an act or omission directed at restricting competition is committed outside the territory of Estonia but restricts competition within the territory of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolev seadus ei reguleeri suhteid t&ouml;&ouml;j&otilde;uturul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) This Act does not regulate relationships in the labour market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 2. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 2. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettev&otilde;tja </eesti>
<inglise>Undertaking </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ettev&otilde;tja k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on &auml;ri&uuml;hing, f&uuml;&uuml;silisest isikust ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i muu majandus- v&otilde;i kutsetegevuses osalev isik v&otilde;i juriidiliseks isikuks mitteolev &uuml;hendus v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja huvides tegutsev isik. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, an undertaking is a company, sole proprietor, any other person engaged in economic or professional activities, an association which is not a legal person, or a person acting in the interests of an undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui avalik-&otilde;iguslikku funktsiooni t&auml;itev isik, riik v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksus osaleb kaubaturul, kohaldatakse neile ettev&otilde;tjate kohta k&auml;ivaid s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provisions concerning undertakings apply to persons who perform functions in public law and to the state and local governments if they participate in a goods market. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigile, kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksusele ja Eesti Pangale ei laiene k&auml;esoleva seaduse 9. peat&uuml;ki s&auml;tted. </eesti>
<inglise>The provisions of Chapter 9 of this Act do not extend to the state, local governments or the Bank of Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses v&otilde;ib lugeda &uuml;heks ettev&otilde;tjaks samal kaubaturul tegutsevaid &uuml;hte kontserni kuuluvaid ettev&otilde;tjaid v&otilde;i teisi valitseva m&otilde;ju kaudu &uuml;ksteisega seotud ettev&otilde;tjaid, kui nende ettev&otilde;tjate vahel puudub konkurents. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) For the purposes of this Act, undertakings which operate in the same goods market and belong to the same group of companies or other undertakings which are connected through control may be deemed to be one undertaking if there is no competition between such undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Valitsev m&otilde;ju on v&otilde;imalus &uuml;he v&otilde;i mitme ettev&otilde;tja poolt &uuml;hiselt teise ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku poolt ettev&otilde;tja aktsiate v&otilde;i osade omamise kaudu, lepingu, tehingu v&otilde;i p&otilde;hikirja alusel v&otilde;i muul viisil otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt m&otilde;jutada teist ettev&otilde;tjat, mis v&otilde;ib seisneda &otilde;iguses: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Control is the opportunity for one undertaking or several undertakings jointly or for a natural person, by purchasing shares and on the basis of a contract, transaction or articles of association or by any other means, to exercise direct or indirect influence on another undertaking which may consist of a right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) oluliselt m&otilde;jutada teise ettev&otilde;tja juhtorganite koosseisu, t&ouml;&ouml;d v&otilde;i otsuste tegemist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) exercise significant influence on the composition, work or decision-making of the management bodies of the other undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kasutada ja k&auml;sutada teise ettev&otilde;tja kogu vara v&otilde;i olulist osa sellest. </eesti>
<inglise>2) use or dispose of all or a significant proportion of the assets of the other undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaubaturg </eesti>
<inglise>Goods market </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kaubaturg on hinna, kvaliteedi, tehniliste omaduste, realiseerimis- ning kasutustingimuste, tarbimis- ja muude omaduste poolest ostja seisukohalt omavahel vahetatavate v&otilde;i asendatavate (edaspidi asendatavate) kaupade k&auml;ibimise ala kogu Eesti territooriumil v&otilde;i selle osal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A goods market is an area covering the whole of the territory of Estonia or a part thereof where goods which are regarded as interchangeable or substitutable (hereinafter substitutable) by the buyer by reason of price, quality, technical characteristics, conditions of sale or use, consumption or other characteristics are circulated. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaubaturu piiritlemisel arvestatakse asendatavate kaupade k&auml;ivet &uuml;ldjuhul rahalises v&auml;ljenduses. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In order to define a goods market, the turnover of substitutable goods shall, as a rule, be assessed in money. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui see ei ole v&otilde;imalik v&otilde;i otstarbekas, v&otilde;ib kaubaturu mahtu ja sellel tegutseva ettev&otilde;tja turuosa arvestada m&otilde;ne muu v&otilde;rreldava n&auml;itaja alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>If this is not possible or expedient, the market size and the market shares of the undertakings participating in the goods market may be assessed on the basis of other comparable indicators. </inglise>
<eesti>2. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 2 </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkuleppe, koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuse ja ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;henduse otsuse keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on Agreements, Concerted Practices and Decisions by Associations of Undertakings </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsi kahjustava kokkuleppe, koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuse ja ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;henduse otsuse keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on agreements, concerted practices and decisions by associations of undertakings which restrict competition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Keelatud on konkurentsi kahjustava eesm&auml;rgi v&otilde;i tagaj&auml;rjega ettev&otilde;tjatevaheline kokkulepe, koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevus ja ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;henduse otsus (edaspidi kokkulepe, tegevus ja otsus), sealhulgas: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The following are prohibited: agreements between undertakings, concerted practices, and decisions by associations of undertakings (hereinafter agreements, practices and decisions) which have as their object or effect the restriction of competition, including those which: </inglise>
<eesti>1) otsene v&otilde;i kaudne kolmandate isikute suhtes hinna- ja muude kauplemistingimuste kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ramine, sealhulgas kauba hinna, tariifi, tasu, juurde-, alla- v&otilde;i mahahindluse, abonement-, lisa- v&otilde;i t&auml;iendava tasu, intressim&auml;&auml;ra, rendi v&otilde;i &uuml;&uuml;ri m&auml;&auml;ramine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) directly or indirectly fix prices or any other trading conditions, including prices of goods, tariffs, fees, mark-ups, discounts, rebates, basic fees, premiums, additional fees, interest rates, rent or lease payments applicable to third parties; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tootmise, teenindamise, kaubaturu, tehnilise arengu v&otilde;i investeerimise piiramine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) limit production, service, goods markets, technical development or investment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kaubaturu v&otilde;i varustusallika jagamine, sealhulgas kolmandale isikule kaubaturule p&auml;&auml;su piiramine v&otilde;i p&uuml;&uuml;d teda sealt v&auml;lja t&otilde;rjuda; </eesti>
<inglise>3) share goods markets or sources of supply, including restriction of access by a third party to a goods market or any attempt to exclude the person from the market; </inglise>
<eesti>4) konkurentsi kahjustava teabe vahetamine; </eesti>
<inglise>4) exchange information which restricts competition; </inglise>
<eesti>5) v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rsete kokkulepete puhul erinevate tingimuste rakendamises kokkuleppimine, millega &auml;ripartnerid pannakse ebasoodsasse konkurentsiolukorda; </eesti>
<inglise>5) agree on the application of dissimilar conditions to equivalent agreements, thereby placing other trading parties at a competitive disadvantage; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimise eelduseks tingimuse seadmine, et teine pool v&otilde;tab endale kokkuleppe objektiga mitteseotud lisakohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>6) make entry into an agreement subject to acceptance by the other parties of supplementary obligations which have no connection with the subject of such agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) P&otilde;llumajandustootjate kokkuleppele, tegevusele ja nende &uuml;henduste otsusele, mis k&auml;sitleb p&otilde;llumajandussaaduse tootmist ja m&uuml;&uuml;ki ning &uuml;histe vahendite kasutamist, ei kohaldu k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktid 2-6, kui selle kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsusega konkurentsi oluliselt ei kahjustata. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Clauses (1) 2) -6) of this section do not apply to agreements and practices of agricultural producers or to decisions by associations of agricultural producers, which concern the production or sale of agricultural products or the use of joint facilities, unless competition is substantially restricted by such agreements, practices or decisions. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus </eesti>
<inglise>Agreements, practices or decisions of minor importance </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 4 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 2-6 s&auml;testatut ei kohaldata v&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega kokkuleppele, tegevusele ja otsusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The provisions of clauses 4 (1) 2) -6) of this Act do not apply to agreements, practices and decisions of minor importance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) V&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega on kokkulepe, tegevus ja otsus, kui kokkulepet s&otilde;lmivate, koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevate v&otilde;i otsust vastuv&otilde;tvate ettev&otilde;tjate k&auml;ivete summaarne osat&auml;htsus ei ole kaubaturul: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Agreements, practices or decisions are considered to be of minor importance if the combined market share of the total turnover of the undertakings which enter into the agreement, engage in concerted practices or adopt the relevant decision does not exceed: </inglise>
<eesti>1) vertikaalse kokkuleppe, tegevuse ja otsuse puhul suurem kui 10 protsenti; </eesti>
<inglise>1) 10 per cent in the case of a vertical agreement, practice or decision; </inglise>
<eesti>2) horisontaalse kokkuleppe, tegevuse ja otsuse puhul suurem kui 5 protsenti; </eesti>
<inglise>2) 5 per cent in the case of a horizontal agreement, practice or decision; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kokkuleppe, tegevuse ja otsuse puhul, milles esinevad &uuml;heaegselt nii vertikaalse kui horisontaalse kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse tunnused, suurem kui 5 protsenti. </eesti>
<inglise>3) 5 per cent in the case of an agreement, practice or decision which includes concurrently the characteristics of both vertical and horizontal agreements, practices or decisions. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vertikaalne on ettev&otilde;tjate kokkulepe, nende koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevus ja ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;henduse otsus siis, kui nimetatud ettev&otilde;tjad tegutsevad tootmise v&otilde;i turustamise erinevatel tasanditel (n&auml;iteks tooraine v&otilde;i valmiskauba tootmine, jae- v&otilde;i hulgiturustus). </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Agreements by undertakings, concerted practices of undertakings or decisions by associations of undertakings are considered to be vertical if the undertakings operate at different levels of the production or distribution chain (for example the production of raw materials or finished goods, or retail or wholesale distribution). </inglise>
<eesti>Horisontaalne on ettev&otilde;tjate kokkulepe, nende koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevus ja ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;henduse otsus siis, kui nimetatud ettev&otilde;tjad tegutsevad tootmise v&otilde;i turustamise samal tasandil konkurentidena. </eesti>
<inglise>Agreements by undertakings, concerted practices of undertakings or decisions by associations of undertakings are considered to be horizontal if the undertakings operate as competitors at the same level of the production or distribution chain. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) V&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega on kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus siis, kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud tingimused on t&auml;idetud selle kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse kogu toimimise aja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Agreements, practices or decisions are deemed to be of minor importance if the conditions provided for in subsection (2) of this section are fulfilled during the whole period of effect of the agreement, practice or decision. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 6. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 6. </inglise>
<eesti>Erand </eesti>
<inglise>Exemption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Erand on ettev&otilde;tja taotlusel Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusega antud luba k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 4 nimetatud kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimiseks, koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuseks v&otilde;i otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An exemption is permission granted at the request of an undertaking by a decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy to enter into an agreement, engage in concerted practices or adopt a decision specified in &sect; 4 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud loa v&otilde;ib anda juhul, kui kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The permission specified in subsection (1) of this section may be granted if the agreement, practice or decision: </inglise>
<eesti>1) aitab parandada kaupade tootmist v&otilde;i turustamist v&otilde;i edendada tehnilist v&otilde;i majanduslikku progressi v&otilde;i kaitsta keskkonda, v&otilde;imaldades tarbijatel saada sellest tulenevast kasust &otilde;iglase osa; </eesti>
<inglise>1) contributes to improving the production or distribution of goods or to promoting technical or economic progress or to protecting the environment, while allowing consumers a fair share of the resulting benefit; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ei kehtesta kokkulepet s&otilde;lmivatele, koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevatele v&otilde;i otsust vastuv&otilde;tvatele ettev&otilde;tjatele piiranguid, mis ei ole h&auml;davajalikud k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 1 nimetatud eesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) does not impose on the undertakings which enter into the agreement, engage in concerted practices or adopt the decision any restrictions which are not indispensable to the attainment of the objectives specified in clause 1) of this subsection; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ei anna kokkulepet s&otilde;lmivatele, koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevatele v&otilde;i otsust vastuv&otilde;tvatele ettev&otilde;tjatele v&otilde;imalust k&otilde;rvaldada konkurentsi kaubaturu olulise osa suhtes. </eesti>
<inglise>3) does not afford the undertakings which enter into the agreement, engage in concerted practices or adopt the decision the possibility of eliminating competition in respect of a substantial part of the goods market. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud loa saamiseks peavad olema t&auml;idetud k&otilde;ik l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud tingimused. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to obtain the permission specified in subsection (1) of this section, all the conditions provided for in subsection (2) must be fulfilled. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 7. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 7. </inglise>
<eesti>Grupierand </eesti>
<inglise>Block exemption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Grupierand on rahandusministri ettepanekul Vabariigi Valitsuse m&auml;&auml;rusega antud &uuml;ldine luba k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 s&auml;testatud tingimustele vastavate teatud liiki konkurentsi kahjustavate v&otilde;i kahjustada v&otilde;ivate kokkulepete s&otilde;lmimiseks, koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuseks v&otilde;i otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A block exemption is general permission granted by a regulation of the Government of the Republic on the proposal of the Minister of Finance to enter into a certain category of agreements, engage in a certain category of concerted practices or adopt a certain category of decisions which complies with the conditions provided for in &sect; 6 of this Act and restricts or may restrict competition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Grupierand kehtestatakse t&auml;htajalisena ja selles v&otilde;idakse m&auml;&auml;rata: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A block exemption is established for a specified term and may designate: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse liigi nimetus, mille suhtes grupierand kohaldub; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name of the category of agreements, practices or decisions to which the block exemption applies; </inglise>
<eesti>2) piirangud v&otilde;i tingimused, mis sellises kokkuleppes, tegevuses v&otilde;i otsuses ei tohi sisalduda; </eesti>
<inglise>2) restrictions or conditions which shall not be included in such agreements, practices or decisions; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tingimused, mis peavad sellises kokkuleppes, tegevuses v&otilde;i otsuses sisalduma, ning piirangud ja tingimused, mis v&otilde;ivad sellises kokkuleppes, tegevuses v&otilde;i otsuses sisalduda; </eesti>
<inglise>3) conditions which must be included in such agreements, practices or decisions, and restrictions and conditions which may be included in such agreements, practices or decisions; </inglise>
<eesti>4) muud tingimused, millele kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus peab vastama. </eesti>
<inglise>4) other conditions which such agreements, practices or decisions must comply with. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 alusel kehtestatud grupierand ei kohaldu: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A block exemption established on the basis of subsection (1) of this section does not apply: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kaubaturgu valitseva ettev&otilde;tja suhtes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to an undertaking in a dominant position; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kui kaubaturul, mida kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus m&otilde;jutab, praktiliselt puudub konkurents. </eesti>
<inglise>2) if competition is virtually non-existent in the goods market affected by the agreement, practices or decision. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 8. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 8. </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkuleppe ja otsuse kehtetus </eesti>
<inglise>Invalidity of agreements or decisions </inglise>
<eesti>Kokkulepe ja otsus v&otilde;i nende osa, millel on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 4 nimetatud eesm&auml;rgid v&otilde;i tagaj&auml;rjed ning millele ei ole &sect; 6 v&otilde;i 7 alusel antud luba, on t&uuml;hine, v&auml;lja arvatud &sect;-le 5 vastav kokkulepe ja otsus. </eesti>
<inglise>Any agreement or decision or a part thereof which has as its object or effect the consequences specified in &sect; 4 of this Act and with regard to which permission has not been granted on the basis of &sect; 6 or 7 of this Act is void unless it complies with &sect; 5 of this Act. </inglise>
