<inglise>Chapter 3 </inglise>
<eesti>Erandi andmise menetlus </eesti>
<inglise>Procedure for Grant of Exemptions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 9. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 9. </inglise>
<eesti>Eranditaotluse esitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Submission of applications for exemption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 s&auml;testatud erandi saamiseks tuleb esitada Konkurentsiametile eranditaotlus enne kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimist, koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuse alustamist v&otilde;i otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to obtain an exemption provided for in &sect; 6 of this Act, an application for exemption shall be submitted to the Competition Board before entry into the relevant agreement, commencement of the concerted practices or adoption of the relevant decision. </inglise>
<eesti>Eranditaotluse v&otilde;ib esitada ka erandit vajava kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimisest v&otilde;i otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmisest kuue kuu jooksul, seejuures on vastav kokkulepe v&otilde;i otsus v&otilde;i nende konkurentsi kahjustav osa kuni erandi andmiseni kehtetu. </eesti>
<inglise>An application for exemption may also be submitted within six months after entry into an agreement or adoption of a decision which requires an exemption, and the corresponding agreement or decision or a part thereof which restricts competition shall be void until the grant of the exemption. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eranditaotlus kokkuleppe, otsuse v&otilde;i nende osa v&otilde;i tegevuse kohta, mis ei olnud kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimisel, tegevuse alustamisel v&otilde;i otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmisel k&auml;esoleva seadusega vastuolus, tuleb esitada kolme kuu jooksul, alates asjaolude ilmnemisest, mille t&otilde;ttu kokkulepe v&otilde;i otsus v&otilde;i selle osa v&otilde;i tegevus osutub k&auml;esoleva seadusega vastuolus olevaks, v&otilde;i ajast, millal nende olemasolust oleks pidanud teada saama. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An application for exemption with regard to an agreement, decision or a part thereof or practices which was not in conflict with this Act upon entry into the agreement, commencement of the practices or adoption of the decision shall be submitted within three months as of the appearance of circumstances due to which the agreement or decision or a part thereof or the practices becomes contrary to this Act or within three months as of the time such circumstances should have become evident. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastav kokkulepe v&otilde;i otsus v&otilde;i selle osa on vastavate asjaolude ilmnemisest kuni erandi andmiseni kehtetu. </eesti>
<inglise>Such agreement or decision or a part thereof is invalid from the appearance of the circumstances until the grant of the exemption. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eranditaotluse esitavad kokkuleppe s&otilde;lminud v&otilde;i koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsenud v&otilde;i otsuse vastuv&otilde;tnud ettev&otilde;tjad &uuml;hiselt v&otilde;i &uuml;ks nendest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An application for exemption shall be submitted jointly by the undertakings which entered into an agreement, engaged in concerted practices or adopted a decision, or by one of the undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud isikud v&otilde;ivad &uuml;hiselt v&otilde;i eraldi eranditaotluse tagasi v&otilde;tta igal ajal kuni erandi andmiseni, esitades sellekohase kirjaliku avalduse, kusjuures nimetatud avalduse esitaja ei pea olema sama isik, kes eranditaotluse esitas. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Persons specified in subsection (3) of this section may withdraw an application for exemption jointly or separately at any time before the grant of the exemption by submitting a corresponding written petition, and the person submitting the petition need not be the same as the person who submitted the application for exemption. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 10. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 10. </inglise>
<eesti>Eranditaotlusele esitatavad n&otilde;uded </eesti>
<inglise>Requirements for applications for exemption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) N&otilde;uded eranditaotlusele, erandi kehtivuse t&auml;htaja pikendamiseks esitatavale taotlusele ja taotluse esitamise korra kehtestab rahandusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The requirements for applications for exemption, the requirements for applications for extension of the term of an exemption, and the procedure for submission of applications shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti n&otilde;udmisel peab eranditaotleja andma selgitusi ning esitama tutvumiseks dokumentide originaalid v&otilde;i nende koopiad v&otilde;i &auml;rakirjad, mille vastavust originaalile kinnitab nende esitaja oma allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>At the request of the Competition Board, an applicant for an exemption shall provide explanations and submit for examination original documents or true copies or transcripts thereof, certified by the signature of the person submitting the copies or transcripts. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui eranditaotluses sisalduv v&otilde;i sellega seoses esitatud teave on eba&otilde;ige, mittet&auml;ielik v&otilde;i eksitav, m&auml;&auml;rab Konkurentsiamet taotlejale t&auml;htaja puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If information contained in an application for an exemption or information relating to the application is incorrect, incomplete or misleading, the Competition Board shall set a deadline for the applicant to eliminate the deficiencies. </inglise>
<eesti>P&auml;rast puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamist saadab Konkurentsiamet eranditaotluse esitajale vastava kinnituse, mille v&auml;ljasaatmisest algab ka k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 11 l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaegade kulgemine. </eesti>
<inglise>After elimination of the deficiencies, the Competition Board shall send corresponding confirmation to the applicant for the exemption, and the running of the terms provided for in subsections 11 (2) and (3) of this Act shall commence as of the date on which the confirmation is sent. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Isik, kelle kasuks on erand antud, ja isik, kes erandi andmise otsust taotleb, peab olulistest muudatustest eranditaotluses esitatud andmetes viivitamata Konkurentsiametile kirjalikult teatama. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The person for whose benefit an exemption is granted and the person who applies for a decision on the grant of the exemption shall immediately give written notice to the Competition Board of any substantial changes in the information presented in the application for the exemption. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teabe juurde, mida eranditaotluse esitaja v&otilde;i teine kokkuleppe pool peab &auml;risaladuseks, teeb ta vastava m&auml;rke. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An applicant for exemption or the other party to the agreement shall indicate any information which the applicant or other party deems to be a business secret. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 11. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 11. </inglise>
<eesti>Eranditaotluse lahendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Processing of applications for exemption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja teeb eranditaotluse kohta &uuml;he j&auml;rgmistest otsustest: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall make one of the following decisions concerning an application for an exemption: </inglise>
<eesti>1) annab erandi, kui ta leiab, et taotluse aluseks olev kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus on vastavuses k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 s&auml;testatud tingimustega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to grant the exemption if he or she finds that the agreement, practice or decision which is the basis for the application complies with the conditions provided for in &sect; 6 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) keeldub erandi andmisest, kui ta leiab, et taotluse aluseks olev kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 s&auml;testatud tingimustele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to refuse to grant the exemption if he or she finds that the agreement, practice or decision which is the basis for the application does not comply with the conditions provided for in &sect; 6 of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) l&otilde;petab menetluse, kui eranditaotlus on tagasi v&otilde;etud v&otilde;i kui Konkurentsiameti m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks ei ole eranditaotleja oma taotluses puudusi k&otilde;rvaldanud v&otilde;i ei ole Konkurentsiameti n&otilde;utud teavet esitanud; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to terminate the proceedings if the application for the exemption has been withdrawn, or if the applicant for the exemption has failed to eliminate the deficiencies in the application within the term specified by the Competition Board or to submit the information requested by the Competition Board; </inglise>
<eesti>4) l&otilde;petab menetluse erandit andmata, tunnistades kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse erandit mittevajavaks, kuna tegemist ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 4 s&auml;testatud kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsusega v&otilde;i kui kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus ei vaja erandit k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 5 s&auml;testatud alustel v&otilde;i kui kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus vastab grupierandile; 5) algatab eranditaotluse kohta t&auml;iendava menetluse, kui ta leiab, et taotluse aluseks oleva kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse sobivus erandi saamiseks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 6 alusel on kaheldav ning otsustamiseks on vajalik saada t&auml;iendavat teavet v&otilde;i teostada t&auml;iendavat kontrolli. </eesti>
<inglise>4) to terminate the proceedings without granting the exemption and to declare that the agreement, practice or decision does not require an exemption as it does not fall within &sect; 4 of this Act or does not require an exemption on the bases specified in &sect; 5 of this Act or requires a group exemption; 5) to initiate supplementary proceedings concerning the application for the exemption if he or she finds that it is doubtful whether the agreement, practice or decision which is the basis for the application qualifies for an exemption pursuant to &sect; 6 of this Act and if it is necessary to obtain additional information or conduct a supplementary examination in order to make the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja teeb &uuml;he k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-4 s&auml;testatud otsustest kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast kogu teabe saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall make one of the decisions provided for in clauses (1) 1) -4) of this section within two months after receiving all the information. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsustab algatada t&auml;iendava menetluse k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 5 alusel, teatab ta sellest kirjalikult erandi taotlejatele ning teeb &uuml;he l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-3 s&auml;testatud otsustest kuue kuu jooksul p&auml;rast kogu teabe saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy decides to initiate supplementary proceedings on the basis of clause (1) 5) of this section, he or she shall notify the applicant for the exemption in writing and make one of the decisions provided for in clause (1) 1) -3) within six months after receiving all the information. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaegu v&otilde;ib Konkurentsiamet pikendada &uuml;ksnes eranditaotleja kirjalikul n&otilde;usolekul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Competition Board may extend the terms provided for in subsections (2) and (3) of this section only with the written consent of the applicant for exemption. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 12. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 12. </inglise>
<eesti>Erandi andmise otsused </eesti>
<inglise>Decision to grant exemption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 11 l&otilde;ikes 1 ja k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud otsus on kirjalik ja sisaldab p&otilde;hjendust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Decisions provided for in subsection 11 (1) of this Act and subsection (5) of this section shall be made in writing and contain the reasons for the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Erandi andmise otsus v&otilde;ib sisaldada kokkulepet s&otilde;lmivatele, koosk&otilde;lastatult tegutsevatele v&otilde;i otsust vastuv&otilde;tvatele ettev&otilde;tjatele tingimusi v&otilde;i kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A decision to grant an exemption may contain conditions or obligations applicable to the undertakings which enter into the agreement, engage in the concerted practices or adopt the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib anda erandi kuni viieks aastaks, kusjuures m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemisel v&otilde;ib erandi kehtivuse t&auml;htaega pikendada erandi andmise otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may grant an exemption for up to five years, and upon expiry of the specified term, the term of the exemption may be extended by a decision to grant an exemption. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Taotlus erandi kehtivuse t&auml;htaja pikendamiseks esitatakse vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 10 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud m&auml;&auml;rusele v&auml;hemalt kuus kuud enne otsuses toodud erandi kehtivuse t&auml;htaja l&otilde;ppemist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) An application for extension of the term of an exemption shall be submitted according to the regulation specified in subsection 10 (1) of this Act at least six months before the expiry of the term of the exemption specified in the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja tunnistab erandi andmise otsuse kehtetuks v&otilde;i muudab seda s&otilde;ltuvalt konkurentsiolukorrast konkreetsel juhul, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall revoke a decision to grant an exemption or shall amend the decision depending on the competitive situation in each specific case if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on toimunud olulisi muutusi erandi andmise aluseks olnud andmetes v&otilde;i tingimustes; </eesti>
<inglise>1) substantial changes have occurred in the information or conditions which were the basis for granting the exemption; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ei t&auml;ideta erandi andmise otsusega pandud kohustusi v&otilde;i tingimusi; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the conditions or obligations attached to the decision to grant the exemption have not been complied with; </inglise>
<eesti>3) erand anti mittet&auml;ielike v&otilde;i eba&otilde;igete andmete alusel ja erandi saanud kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus ei vasta k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 6 s&auml;testatud tingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the exemption was granted on the basis of incomplete or incorrect information and the agreement, practice or decision concerning which the exemption was granted does not comply with the conditions provided for in &sect; 6 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&otilde;igi k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 11 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 1 ja l&otilde;ike 3 ning k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 5 alusel tehtud otsuste kohta avaldab Konkurentsiamet teadaande v&auml;ljaandes Ametlikud Teadaanded. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The Competition Board shall publish a notice concerning each decision made pursuant to clause 11 (1) 1) or subsection 11 (3) of this Act or subsection (5) of this section in the official publication Ametlikud Teadaanded (2). </inglise>
<eesti>4. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Turguvalitsev ettev&otilde;tja </eesti>
<inglise>Undertaking in Dominant Position </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 13. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 13. </inglise>
<eesti>Turguvalitseva ettev&otilde;tja m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of undertaking in dominant position </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Turguvalitsev ettev&otilde;tja k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses on ettev&otilde;tja, kellele kuulub kaubaturul v&auml;hemalt 40 protsenti k&auml;ibest v&otilde;i kelle positsioon v&otilde;imaldab tal sellel kaubaturul tegutseda arvestataval m&auml;&auml;ral s&otilde;ltumatult konkurentidest, varustajatest ja ostjatest. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, an undertaking in a dominant position is an undertaking which accounts for at least 40 per cent of the turnover in the goods market or whose position enables the undertaking to operate in the market to an appreciable extent independently of competitors, suppliers and buyers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Turguvalitsev ettev&otilde;tja on ka k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-des 14 ja 15 s&auml;testatud eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omav ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Undertakings with special or exclusive rights or in control of essential facilities specified in &sect;&sect; 14 and 15 of this Act are also undertakings in a dominant position. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 14. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 14. </inglise>
<eesti>Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust omav ettev&otilde;tja </eesti>
<inglise>Undertaking with special or exclusive rights </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igusena k&auml;sitatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuse poolt ettev&otilde;tjale antud &otilde;igust, mis v&otilde;imaldab tal olla kaubaturul teiste ettev&otilde;tjatega v&otilde;rreldes eelisseisundis v&otilde;i ainsaks ettev&otilde;tjaks sellel kaubaturul. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, special or exclusive rights are rights granted to an undertaking by the state or a local government which enable the undertaking to have a competitive advantage over other undertakings in a goods market or to be the only undertaking in the market. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;iguse andmiseks avaliku konkursi korraldamise korra kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for the organisation of public competitions for granting special or exclusive rights shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;iguse andmise aluseks olev &otilde;igusakt ei s&auml;testa eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;iguse andmise korda, tuleb vastava &otilde;iguse andmiseks korraldada avalik konkurss Vabariigi Valitsuse kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>If legislation on the basis of which special or exclusive rights are granted does not provide the procedure for the grant of a special or exclusive right, a public competition for the grant of such right shall be organised pursuant to the procedure established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>Olulist vahendit omav ettev&otilde;tja </eesti>
<inglise>Undertaking controlling essential facility </inglise>
<eesti>Olulist vahendit, sealhulgas loomulikku monopoli omavaks loetakse ettev&otilde;tja, kelle omandis, valduses v&otilde;i opereerimisel on v&otilde;rgustik, infrastruktuur v&otilde;i muu oluline vahend, mida teisel isikul ei ole v&otilde;imalik v&otilde;i ei ole majanduslikult otstarbekas dubleerida, kuid millele juurdep&auml;&auml;suta v&otilde;i mille olemasoluta ei ole v&otilde;imalik kaubaturul tegutseda. </eesti>
<inglise>An undertaking is deemed to control essential facilities or to have a natural monopoly if it owns, possesses or operates a network, infrastructure or any other essential facility which other persons cannot duplicate or for whom it is economically inexpedient to duplicate but without access to which or the existence of which it is impossible to operate in the goods market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>Turguvalitseva ettev&otilde;tja seisundi kuritarvitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Abuse of dominant position </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud on turguvalitseva ettev&otilde;tja poolt oma seisundi otsene v&otilde;i kaudne kuritarvitamine kaubaturul, sealhulgas: </eesti>
<inglise>The following are prohibited: any direct or indirect abuse by an undertaking in a dominant position of his or her position in the goods market, including: </inglise>
<eesti>1) otsene v&otilde;i kaudne eba&otilde;iglaste ostu- v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;gihindade v&otilde;i muude eba&otilde;iglaste &auml;ritingimuste kehtestamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) directly or indirectly imposing unfair purchase or selling prices or other unfair trading conditions; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tootmise, teenindamise, kaubaturu, tehnilise arengu v&otilde;i investeerimise piiramine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) limiting production, service, goods markets, technical development or investment; </inglise>
<eesti>3) v&otilde;rdv&auml;&auml;rsete kokkulepete s&otilde;lmimisel erinevate tingimuste pakkumine v&otilde;i rakendamine erinevatele &auml;ripartneritele, pannes m&otilde;ne neist sellega ebasoodsasse konkurentsiolukorda; </eesti>
<inglise>3) offering or applying dissimilar conditions to equivalent agreements with other trading parties, thereby placing some of them at a competitive disadvantage; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimise eelduseks tingimuse seadmine, et teine pool v&otilde;tab endale kokkuleppe objektiga mitteseotud lisakohustusi; </eesti>
<inglise>4) making entry into an agreement subject to acceptance by the other parties of supplementary obligations which have no connection with the subject of such agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>5) ettev&otilde;tja sundimine endaga v&otilde;i teise ettev&otilde;tjaga koondumiseks, konkurentsi kahjustava kokkuleppe s&otilde;lmimiseks, koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuseks v&otilde;i otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>5) forcing an undertaking to concentrate, enter into an agreement which restricts competition, engage in concerted practices or adopt a decision together with the undertaking or another undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>6) p&otilde;hjendamatu keeldumine kauba m&uuml;&uuml;misest v&otilde;i ostmisest; </eesti>
<inglise>6) unjustified refusal to sell or buy goods; </inglise>
<eesti>7) eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omava ettev&otilde;tja poolt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 18 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 1 nimetatud kohustuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmine. </eesti>
<inglise>7) failure by an undertaking with special or exclusive rights or in control of essential facilities to perform the obligation specified in clause 18 (1) 1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omava ettev&otilde;tja tegevuse piirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Restrictions on activities of undertakings with special or exclusive rights or in control of essential facilities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust omavale ettev&otilde;tjale v&otilde;ib talle selle &otilde;iguse andnud riigiasutus v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksus m&auml;&auml;rata kasutatavad hinnad v&otilde;i kehtestada muid tingimusi v&otilde;i kohustusi, et selle ettev&otilde;tja kaupade ostjad v&otilde;i sellele ettev&otilde;tjale kaupade m&uuml;&uuml;jad ei satuks oluliselt halvemasse olukorda kui siis, kui antud valdkonnas toimiks vaba konkurents. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The state agency or local government which grants special or exclusive rights to an undertaking may designate the prices to be used or impose other conditions or obligations on the undertaking so that the buyers of the goods of such undertaking or sellers of goods to such undertaking are not placed in a substantially worse situation than they would be if competition were present in the corresponding area of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Olulist vahendit omavale ettev&otilde;tjale v&otilde;ib seadusega m&auml;&auml;ratud riigiasutus, Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalituse territooriumi piires teenust osutava olulist vahendit omava ettev&otilde;tja korral kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksus m&auml;&auml;rata kasutatavad hinnad v&otilde;i kehtestada muid tingimusi v&otilde;i kohustusi, et selle ettev&otilde;tja kaupade ostjad v&otilde;i sellele ettev&otilde;tjale kaupade m&uuml;&uuml;jad ei satuks oluliselt halvemasse olukorda kui siis, kui antud valdkonnas toimiks vaba konkurents. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A state agency prescribed by law, the Government of the Republic or, in the case of an undertaking in control of essential facilities which provides services within the territory of a local government, the local government may designate the prices to be used by an undertaking in control of essential facilities or impose other conditions or obligations on the undertaking so that the buyers of the goods of such undertaking or sellers of goods to such undertaking are not placed in a substantially worse situation than they would be if competition were present in the corresponding area of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;ib kehtestada teatud liiki eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omavatele ettev&otilde;tjatele hindade reguleerimise korra, juhul kui seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktiga vastavat korda kehtestatud ei ole. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the procedure for price regulation applicable to undertakings with certain categories of special or exclusive rights or in control of essential facilities has not been established by an Act or legislation established on the basis thereof, the Government of the Republic may establish the corresponding procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksus v&otilde;ib kehtestada kohaliku omavalitsuse territooriumil teenuseid osutavatele eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omavatele ettev&otilde;tjatele hindade reguleerimise korra, juhul kui seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel antud &otilde;igusaktiga vastavat korda kehtestatud ei ole v&otilde;i kui see kord neile ettev&otilde;tjatele ei laiene. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the procedure for price regulation applicable to undertakings with special or exclusive rights or in control of essential facilities which provide services within the territory of a local government has not been established by an Act or legislation established on the basis thereof or if the procedure does not extend to such undertakings, the local government may establish the corresponding procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omava ettev&otilde;tja kohustused </eesti>
<inglise>Obligations of undertakings with special or exclusive rights or in control of essential facilities </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omav ettev&otilde;tja on kohustatud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An undertaking with special or exclusive rights or in control of an essential facility shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) lubama teisele ettev&otilde;tjale m&otilde;istlikel ja mittediskrimineerivatel tingimustel juurdep&auml;&auml;su v&otilde;rgustikule, infrastruktuurile v&otilde;i muule olulisele vahendile kaupadega varustamise v&otilde;i nende m&uuml;&uuml;gi eesm&auml;rgil; </eesti>
<inglise>1) permit other undertakings to gain access to the network, infrastructure or other essential facility under reasonable and non-discriminatory conditions for the purposes of the supply or sale of goods; </inglise>
<eesti>2) hoidma raamatupidamises selget vahet erinevate p&otilde;hi- ja lisategevusalade vahel (n&auml;iteks tootmine, edastamine, turustamine ja ettev&otilde;tja muud tegevusalad), tagades sellega majandusarvestuste l&auml;bipaistvuse. </eesti>
<inglise>2) draw a clear distinction in its accounts between primary and secondary activities (for example production, transportation, marketing and other activities of the undertaking), thereby ensuring accounting transparency. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omav ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;ib keelduda lubamast teistele ettev&otilde;tjatele juurdep&auml;&auml;su v&otilde;rgustikule, infrastruktuurile v&otilde;i muule olulisele vahendile, kui keeldumiseks on objektiivsed alused, sealhulgas: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An undertaking with special or exclusive rights or in control of an essential facility may refuse to grant other undertakings access to the network, infrastructure or other essential facility if the refusal is based on objective reasons, including cases where: </inglise>
<eesti>1) on ohustatud antud v&otilde;rgustiku, infrastruktuuri v&otilde;i muu olulise vahendiga &uuml;hendatud seadmete ohutus ja turvalisus ning v&otilde;rgustiku, infrastruktuuri v&otilde;i muu olulise vahendi t&ouml;&ouml; efektiivsus ja turvalisus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the safety and security of the equipment connected with the network, infrastructure or other essential facility or the efficiency and security of the operation of such network, infrastructure or facility are endangered; </inglise>
<eesti>2) on ohustatud v&otilde;rgustiku, infrastruktuuri v&otilde;i muu olulise vahendi terviklikkuse hoidmine v&otilde;i vastastikuses seoses toimimine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) maintenance of the integrity or the inter-operability of the network, infrastructure or other essential facility is endangered; </inglise>
<eesti>3) seadmed, mida soovitakse &uuml;hendada v&otilde;rgustiku, infrastruktuuri v&otilde;i muu olulise vahendiga, ei vasta kehtivatele tehnilistele standarditele v&otilde;i reeglitele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) equipment to be connected to the network, infrastructure or other essential facility is not in conformity with the established technical standards or rules; </inglise>
<eesti>4) juurdep&auml;&auml;su taotleval ettev&otilde;tjal puuduvad tehnilised ja finantsilised v&otilde;imalused ning vahendid, et vajalikul m&auml;&auml;ral efektiivselt ja turvaliselt teenindada vastava v&otilde;rgustiku, infrastruktuuri v&otilde;i muu olulise vahendi kaudu v&otilde;i abil; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the undertaking applying for access lacks the technical and financial capability and resources to provide services efficiently and safely to the necessary extent through or with the assistance of the network, infrastructure or other essential facility; </inglise>
<eesti>5) juurdep&auml;&auml;su taotleval ettev&otilde;tjal puudub seadusega etten&auml;htud luba vastavaks tegevuseks; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the undertaking applying for access does not hold the permit prescribed by law for the corresponding activity; </inglise>
<eesti>6) juurdep&auml;&auml;su tagaj&auml;rjel ei ole tagatud seadusega etten&auml;htud andmete kaitse. </eesti>
<inglise>6) as a result of such access, data protection provided by law is no longer ensured. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumise kontrollimine </eesti>
<inglise>Control of Concentrations </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumine </eesti>
<inglise>Concentration </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koondumine on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Concentration is deemed to arise where: </inglise>
<eesti>1) eelnevalt iseseisvalt tegutsenud ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;hinemine &auml;riseadustiku (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373; 2001, 34, 185) t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) previously independent undertakings merge within the meaning of the Commercial Code (RT I 1995, 26-28, 355; 1998, 91-93, 1500; 1999, 10, 155; 23, 355; 24, 360; 57, 596; 102, 907; 2000, 29, 172; 49, 303; 55, 365; 57, 373; 2001, 34, 185); </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;he ettev&otilde;tja poolt valitseva m&otilde;ju omandamine teise ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema osa &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>2) an undertaking acquires control of the whole or part of another undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ettev&otilde;tjate poolt &uuml;hiselt valitseva m&otilde;ju omandamine kolmanda ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema osa &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>3) undertakings jointly acquire control of the whole or part of a third undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &uuml;he f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku poolt, kes juba omab v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he ettev&otilde;tja &uuml;le valitsevat m&otilde;ju, valitseva m&otilde;ju omandamine teise ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema osa &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a natural person already controlling at least one undertaking acquires control of the whole or part of another undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>5) mitme f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku poolt, kes juba omavad v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he ettev&otilde;tja &uuml;le valitsevat m&otilde;ju, &uuml;hiselt valitseva m&otilde;ju omandamine teise ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema osa &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>5) several natural persons already controlling at least one undertaking jointly acquire control of the whole or part of another undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettev&otilde;tja &uuml;le valitseva m&otilde;ju omandamine k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktide 3 ja 5 t&auml;henduses on ka neis nimetatud isikute poolt &uuml;hise ettev&otilde;tja asutamine, kelle &auml;ritegevus on kavandatud pikaajaliseks ja iseseisvaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The creation, by persons specified in clauses (1) 3) and 5) of this section, of a joint venture performing on a lasting and independent basis is also deemed to be acquisition of control within the meaning of clauses (1) 3) and 5) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud &uuml;hise ettev&otilde;tja asutamise eesm&auml;rgiks v&otilde;i tagaj&auml;rjeks on teda asutanud ettev&otilde;tjate omavahelise konkureeriva k&auml;itumise koosk&otilde;lastamine v&otilde;i tema &auml;ritegevus ei ole kavandatud pikaajaliseks ega iseseisvaks, kohaldatakse sellele tegevusele k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 4 s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the creation of a joint venture specified in subsection (2) of this section has as its object or effect the co-ordination of the competitive behaviour of the founders amongst themselves or if the joint venture does not perform on a lasting and independent basis, the provisions of &sect; 4 of this Act apply to the creation of the joint venture. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ettev&otilde;tja osa k&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki t&auml;henduses on ettev&otilde;tja vara v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja organisatsiooniliselt iseseisev osa, sealhulgas ettev&otilde;te, mis on &auml;ritegevuse aluseks ja millele on selgelt omistatav turuk&auml;ive. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) For the purposes of this Chapter, a part of an undertaking is the assets of the undertaking or an organisationally independent part of the undertaking, including an enterprise which constitutes a basis for business activities and to which market turnover can be clearly attributed. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Koondumiseks ei loeta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud tehinguid, kui need toimuvad kontsernisiseste &uuml;mberkorraldustena. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Transactions specified in subsection (1) of this section are not deemed to be a concentration if the transactions are carried out as an internal restructuring of a group of undertakings. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumise osalised </eesti>
<inglise>Parties to concentration </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumise osaline on: </eesti>
<inglise>The following are parties to a concentration: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;hinev ettev&otilde;tja; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the merging undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti>2) f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja, kes omandab valitseva m&otilde;ju teise ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema osa &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the natural person or undertaking who acquires control of the whole or part of another undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>3) f&uuml;&uuml;silised isikud v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tjad, kes &uuml;hiselt omandavad valitseva m&otilde;ju kolmanda ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema osa &uuml;le; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the natural persons or undertakings who jointly acquire control of the whole or part of a third undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema osa, kelle &uuml;le omandatakse valitsev m&otilde;ju. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the undertaking or a part thereof which is the subject of the acquisition of control. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumise kontrollimise kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of control of concentration </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koondumist kontrollitakse, kui koondumise osaliste eelnenud majandusaasta &uuml;lemaailmsed k&auml;ibed kokku &uuml;letavad 500 miljonit krooni ja v&auml;hemalt kahe koondumise osalise &uuml;lemaailmne k&auml;ive &uuml;letab kummalgi 100 miljonit krooni ning v&auml;hemalt &uuml;he &uuml;hineva ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema osa, kelle &uuml;le omandatakse valitsev m&otilde;ju, &auml;ritegevus toimub Eestis. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A concentration shall be subject to control if, during the previous financial year, the aggregate worldwide turnover of the parties to the concentration exceeded 500 million kroons and the aggregate worldwide turnover of each of at least two parties to the concentration exceeded 100 million kroons and if the business activities of at least one of the merging undertakings or of the whole or part of the undertaking of which control is acquired are carried out in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koondumist ei kontrollita, kui krediidiasutus, finantseerimisasutus, kindlustusandja v&otilde;i v&auml;&auml;rtpaberivahendaja, kelle igap&auml;evaseks &auml;ritegevuseks on v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitehingud kas enda v&otilde;i teiste isikute nimel, omandavad edasim&uuml;&uuml;mise eesm&auml;rgil teise ettev&otilde;tja v&auml;&auml;rtpabereid tingimusel, et nad ei kasuta nende v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitega seotud h&auml;&auml;le&otilde;igust v&auml;&auml;rtpaberid k&auml;ibele lasknud ettev&otilde;tja konkureeriva k&auml;itumise m&otilde;jutamiseks, vaid ainult nimetatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite m&uuml;&uuml;gi ettevalmistamisel ning nende v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite edasim&uuml;&uuml;mine toimub &uuml;he aasta jooksul v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite omandamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A concentration shall not be subject to control if credit institutions, financial institutions, insurers or securities brokers whose normal business activities include transactions and dealing in securities for their own account or for the account of others, acquire securities in an undertaking with a view to reselling them, provided that they do not exercise voting rights in respect of those securities with a view to determining the competitive behaviour of the undertaking which issued the securities and provided that they exercise such voting rights only with a view to preparing the sale of the securities and that any such sale takes place within one year of the date of acquisition. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite m&uuml;&uuml;mine ei ole &uuml;he aasta jooksul v&otilde;imalik, v&otilde;ib Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja oma otsusega pikendada seda t&auml;htaega vastava isiku p&otilde;hjendatud taotluse alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If sale of the securities specified in subsection (2) of this section is not possible within one year, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may extend the term by a decision on the basis of a reasoned application made by the person concerned. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumisele hinnangu andmine </eesti>
<inglise>Appraisal of concentrations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koondumisele hinnangu andmisel l&auml;htutakse vajadusest s&auml;ilitada ja arendada konkurentsi, v&otilde;ttes seejuures arvesse kaubaturgude struktuuri ja nii tegelikku kui ka potentsiaalset konkurentsi kaubaturul, sealhulgas: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Appraisal of a concentration shall be based on the need to maintain and develop competition, taking into account the structure of goods markets and the actual and potential competition in the goods market, including: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koondumise osaliste turupositsiooni, nende majanduslikku ja finantsj&otilde;udu ning konkurentide juurdep&auml;&auml;su kaubaturule; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the market position of the parties to the concentration and their economic and financial power and opportunities for competitors to access the goods market; </inglise>
<eesti>2) juriidilisi v&otilde;i muid sisenemist&otilde;kkeid kaubaturule; </eesti>
<inglise>2) legal or other barriers to entry into the goods market; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kaupade n&otilde;udlust ja pakkumist; </eesti>
<inglise>3) supply and demand trends for the relevant goods; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ostjate, m&uuml;&uuml;jate ja l&otilde;pptarbijate huvisid. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the interests of the buyers, sellers and ultimate consumers. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja keelab koondumise, kui see v&otilde;ib tekitada v&otilde;i tugevdada turguvalitsevat seisundit, mis oluliselt kahjustab konkurentsi kaubaturul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall prohibit a concentration if it may create or strengthen a dominant position as a result of which competition would be significantly restricted in the goods market. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumise osaliste k&auml;ive </eesti>
<inglise>Turnover of parties to concentration </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koondumise osalise k&auml;ive on raamatupidamise seaduse (RT I 1994, 48, 790; 1995, 26-28, 355; 92, 1604; 1996, 40, 773; 42, 811; 49, 953; 1998, 59, 941; 1999, 55, 584; 101, 903) alusel arvutatud koondumisele eelnenud majandusaastal tema poolt m&uuml;&uuml;dud kaupade ja osutatud teenuste realiseerimise netok&auml;ive. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The turnover of a party to a concentration is comprised of the realised net turnover of the goods sold or services provided by the party during the financial year preceding the concentration, calculated pursuant to the Accounting Act (RT I 1994, 48, 790; 1995, 26-28, 355; 92, 1604; 1996, 40, 773; 42, 811; 49, 953; 1998, 59, 941; 1999, 55, 584; 101, 903). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Krediidi- ja finantseerimisasutuste k&auml;ibeks loetakse j&auml;rgmiste sissetulekute summa, millest on maha arvatud k&auml;ibemaks ja tulumaks: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The turnover of a credit or financial institution is deemed to comprise the total amount of the following income items after deduction of value added tax and income tax: </inglise>
<eesti>1) intressitulu ja teised sarnased tulud; </eesti>
<inglise>1) interest income and other similar income; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tulu v&auml;&auml;rtpaberitest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) income from securities; </inglise>
<eesti>3) tulu osalustest ettev&otilde;tjates; </eesti>
<inglise>3) income from holdings in undertakings; </inglise>
<eesti>4) komisjoni- ja teenustasud; </eesti>
<inglise>4) commissions and service charges; </inglise>
<eesti>5) finantsoperatsioonidest saadud puhaskasum; </eesti>
<inglise>5) net profit on financial operations; </inglise>
<eesti>6) muud tegevustulud. </eesti>
<inglise>6) other operating income. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kindlustusandja k&auml;ibeks loetakse bilansiliste kindlustuspreemiate v&auml;&auml;rtus, mis h&otilde;lmab k&otilde;iki saadud ja saadavaid summasid kindlustusandja poolt v&otilde;i nimel v&auml;ljastatud kindlustuslepingute alusel, kaasa arvatud v&auml;ljaminevad edasikindlustuse preemiad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The turnover of an insurer is deemed to comprise the value of gross premiums written which comprises all amounts received and receivable in respect of insurance contracts issued by or on behalf of the insurer, including outgoing reinsurance premiums. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;ibe arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of turnover </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 21 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud koondumise osalise k&auml;ibe arvutamisel lisatakse tema k&auml;ibele j&auml;rgmiste ettev&otilde;tjate k&auml;ive: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The turnover of a party to a concentration specified in subsection 21 (1) of this Act shall be calculated by adding the turnovers of the following undertakings to the turnover of the party: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettev&otilde;tja, kelle &uuml;le koondumise osaline omab valitsevat m&otilde;ju; </eesti>
<inglise>1) undertakings controlled by the party to the concentration; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettev&otilde;tja, kellel on koondumise osalise &uuml;le valitsev m&otilde;ju; </eesti>
<inglise>2) undertakings controlling the party to the concentration; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ettev&otilde;tja, kelle &uuml;le k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 2 nimetatud ettev&otilde;tja omab valitsevat m&otilde;ju; </eesti>
<inglise>3) undertakings controlled by an undertaking specified in clause 2) of this subsection; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ettev&otilde;tja, kelle &uuml;le k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktides 1-3 nimetatud ettev&otilde;tjad &uuml;hiselt omavad valitsevat m&otilde;ju. </eesti>
<inglise>4) undertakings jointly controlled by undertakings specified in clauses 1) -3) of this subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui ettev&otilde;tja &uuml;le omandatakse valitsev m&otilde;ju k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 19 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 2-5 s&auml;testatud viisil, v&otilde;etakse tema k&auml;ibe arvutamisel arvesse ainult selle ettev&otilde;tja ja tema valitseva m&otilde;ju all olevate ettev&otilde;tjate k&auml;ibed. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If control over an undertaking is acquired in a manner provided for in clauses 19 (1) 2) -5) of this Act, the turnover of the undertaking shall be calculated by taking into account only the turnover of such undertaking and the turnovers of the undertakings controlled by the undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui ettev&otilde;tja osa &uuml;le omandatakse valitsev m&otilde;ju k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 19 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 2-5 s&auml;testatud viisil, v&otilde;etakse tema k&auml;ibe arvutamisel arvesse ainult ettev&otilde;tja selle osa k&auml;ive, mille suhtes tehing sooritati. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If control over a part of an undertaking is acquired in a manner provided for in clauses 19 (1) 2) -5) of this Act, the turnover of the undertaking shall be calculated by taking into account the turnover of only such part of the undertaking which is the subject of the transaction. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui kahe v&otilde;i enama tehingu teel omandatakse valitsev m&otilde;ju ettev&otilde;tja &uuml;le v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tja osa &uuml;le, v&otilde;etakse k&auml;ibe arvutamisel arvesse k&otilde;igi nende osade k&auml;ive, mille suhtes sooritati tehingud eelneva kahe aasta jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If control of the whole or part of an undertaking is acquired through two or more transactions, turnover shall be calculated by taking into account the turnovers of all such parts which were subject to transactions during the preceding two years. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui eelneva kahe aasta jooksul on &uuml;ks ja sama ettev&otilde;tja omandanud valitseva m&otilde;ju ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;le, kes tegutsevad Eestis &uuml;hes ja samas majandusharus, peab selle ettev&otilde;tja k&auml;ive, kelle &uuml;le omandatakse valitsev m&otilde;ju, sisaldama ka nende ettev&otilde;tjate k&auml;ivet, kelle &uuml;le on valitsev m&otilde;ju omandatud koondumisele eelneva kahe aasta jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If within the preceding two years one and the same undertaking has acquired control of undertakings which operate in Estonia in one and the same sector of the economy, the turnover of the undertaking of which control is acquired shall include the turnover of the undertakings of which control has been acquired within the two years preceding the concentration. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;ibe arvutamise juhendi kehtestab rahandusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The guidelines for the calculation of turnover shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Eri majandusharudes tegutsevate koondumise osaliste k&auml;ibe arvutamisel v&otilde;ib juhendis ette n&auml;ha erinevaid metoodikaid. </eesti>
<inglise>The guideline may prescribe different methods for calculation of the turnover of parties to a concentration which operate in different sectors of the economy. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumisest teatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Notification of concentrations </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koondumisest, mis kuulub kontrollimisele, teatatakse Konkurentsiametile &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul, arvates: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A concentration subject to control shall be notified to the Competition Board within one week as of: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &uuml;hinemislepingu s&otilde;lmimisest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) entry into the merger agreement; </inglise>
<eesti>2) valitseva m&otilde;ju omandamisest; </eesti>
<inglise>2) acquisition of control; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &uuml;hise valitseva m&otilde;ju omandamisest; </eesti>
<inglise>3) acquisition of joint control; </inglise>
<eesti>4) v&auml;&auml;rtpaberite avaliku ostupakkumise v&auml;ljakuulutamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>4) announcement of the public bid for securities. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koondumisest teatab v&otilde;i teatavad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 19 l&otilde;ike 1: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Notification of a concentration shall be effected: </inglise>
<eesti>1) punktis 1 nimetatud koondumise osalised &uuml;hiselt; </eesti>
<inglise>1) jointly by the parties to a concentration as specified in clause 19 (1) 1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) punktis 2 nimetatud valitsevat m&otilde;ju omandav ettev&otilde;tja; </eesti>
<inglise>2) by an undertaking acquiring control as specified in clause 19 (1) 2) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) punktis 3 nimetatud &uuml;hist valitsevat m&otilde;ju omandavad ettev&otilde;tjad &uuml;hiselt; </eesti>
<inglise>3) jointly by undertakings acquiring joint control as specified in clause 19 (1) 3) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) punktis 4 nimetatud isik, kes omandab valitsevat m&otilde;ju; </eesti>
<inglise>4) by a person acquiring control as specified in clause 19 (1) 4) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) punktis 5 nimetatud &uuml;hist valitsevat m&otilde;ju omandavad isikud &uuml;hiselt. </eesti>
<inglise>5) jointly by persons acquiring joint control as specified in clause 19 (1) 5) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Krediidiasutused, v&auml;&auml;rtpaberivahendajad ja kindlustusandjad teatavad koondumisest k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htajal v&otilde;i mitte hiljem kui &uuml;he n&auml;dala jooksul p&auml;rast vastava ala riikliku j&auml;relevalve asutuselt loa saamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Credit institutions, securities brokers and insurers shall give notification of a concentration within the term provided for in subsection (1) of this section or not later than within one week after obtaining permission from the state supervisory authority in the corresponding field of activity. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumise teade </eesti>
<inglise>Notice of concentration </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koondumise teade esitatakse Konkurentsiametile kirjalikult ja selles sisalduvad: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A notice of concentration shall be submitted to the Competition Board in writing and shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) andmed koondumise osaliste kohta, sealhulgas &auml;rinimed, registrikoodid, kontaktandmed, tegevusalad; </eesti>
<inglise>1) information concerning the parties to the concentration, including business names, registry codes, contact details and areas of activity; </inglise>
<eesti>2) koondumise kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a description of the concentration; </inglise>
<eesti>3) andmed koondumise osaliste eelmise majandusaasta k&auml;ibe kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) data concerning the turnovers of the parties to the concentration during the preceding financial year; </inglise>
<eesti>4) andmed koondumise osalistega samasse kontserni kuuluvate ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 24 l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1-4 nimetatud ettev&otilde;tjate valitseva m&otilde;ju ja osaluse kohta teistes ettev&otilde;tjates; </eesti>
<inglise>4) information concerning control exercised or holdings owned in other undertakings by undertakings specified in clauses 24 (1) 1) -4) of this Act which belong to the same group as the parties to the concentration; </inglise>
<eesti>5) andmed kaubaturgude kohta, sealhulgas andmed koondumise osaliste turuosade, peamiste konkurentide, klientide ja nende turuosade ning kaubaturule sisenemise v&otilde;i sealt lahkumise t&otilde;kete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) information concerning the goods markets, including information concerning the market shares, main competitors, clients and the market shares of the competitors and clients of the parties to the concentration, and concerning barriers to entry into or exit from the goods market; </inglise>
<eesti>6) teate esitaja kirjeldus koondumise m&otilde;just kaubaturule; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a description of the effect of the concentration on the goods market, prepared by the person submitting the notice; </inglise>
<eesti>7) andmed ettev&otilde;tjate &uuml;henduste kohta, kuhu kuulub v&auml;hemalt &uuml;ks koondumise osaline; </eesti>
<inglise>7) information concerning associations of undertakings in which at least one of the parties to the concentration is a member; </inglise>
<eesti>8) koondumisega otseselt seotud ja selle j&otilde;ustamiseks vajalikud konkurentsipiirangud, kui neid esineb, ja p&otilde;hjendus nende vajalikkusest; </eesti>
<inglise>8) restrictions on competition, if any, which are directly related to and necessary for giving effect to the concentration, and the reasons for applying such restrictions; </inglise>
<eesti>9) andmed muude koondumisega seotud asjaolude kohta, kui neid esineb, sealhulgas ettepanekud koondumisega otseselt seotud tingimuste ja kohustuste osas. </eesti>
<inglise>9) information concerning other circumstances, if any, relating to the concentration, including proposals concerning the conditions and obligations directly related to the concentration. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koondumise teatele lisatakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following shall be annexed to a notice of concentration: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koondumise osaliste registreerimisdokumentide &auml;rakirjad riiklikest registritest; </eesti>
<inglise>1) copies of the registration documents of the parties to the concentration from state registers; </inglise>
<eesti>2) dokumendid, mille alusel koondumine j&otilde;ustatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the documents on the basis of which the concentration is put into effect; </inglise>
<eesti>3) koondumise osaliste koondumisele eelnenud majandusaasta aruanded ja raamatupidamisaruanded; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the annual reports and annual accounts of the parties to the concentration for the financial year preceding the concentration; </inglise>
<eesti>4) teate esitaja volitusi t&otilde;endav dokument; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a document certifying the authority of the person submitting the notice; </inglise>
<eesti>5) dokument riigil&otilde;ivu tasumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a document certifying payment of the state fee; </inglise>
<eesti>6) koondumise teatele lisatud dokumentide loetelu. </eesti>
<inglise>6) a list of the documents annexed to the notice of concentration. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Koondumise teatele lisatakse originaaldokumendid v&otilde;i nende t&otilde;estatud &auml;rakirjad. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Documents annexed to a notice of concentration shall be originals or certified copies thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Teatel peab olema selle esitamise kuup&auml;ev ja esitaja allkiri. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A notice shall contain the date of submission of the notice and the signature of the person submitting the notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Koondumise teate esitamise juhendi kehtestab rahandusminister m&auml;&auml;rusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The guidelines for the submission of notices of concentration shall be established by a regulation of the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui teade ei vasta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1-4 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele v&otilde;i l&otilde;ikes 5 nimetatud juhendile, loetakse teade mitteesitatuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If a notice does not meet the requirements provided for in subsections (1) -(4) of this section or the guideline specified in subsection (5) of this section, the notice shall be deemed not to have been submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata t&auml;htaja koondumise teate puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or deputy may establish a deadline for elimination of the deficiencies in a notice of concentration. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib vabastada koondumise osalise m&otilde;nede k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud andmete ja dokumentide esitamise kohustusest, kui need ei ole vajalikud antud koondumise menetlemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may release a party to a concentration from the obligation to submit some of the documents or information specified in subsection (1) or (2) of this section if such documents or information are not necessary for the proceedings concerning the concentration. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Koondumise teates sisalduva teabe juurde, mida koondumisest teataja peab &auml;risaladuseks, teeb ta vastava m&auml;rke. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) The person submitting a notice of concentration shall indicate information contained in the notice which the person deems to be a business secret. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;risaladuseks ei saa lugeda koondumist ennast ja k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1 ja 4 s&auml;testatud teavet. </eesti>
<inglise>The fact of a concentration and the information provided for in clauses (1) 1) and 4) of this section shall not be deemed to be a business secret. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumise menetlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings concerning concentration </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Koondumise teate esitamisest 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Within thirty calendar days as of the submission of a notice of concentration, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teeb koondumiseks loa andmise otsuse, juhul kui kontrollitava koondumise puhul ei esine k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 22 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud asjaolusid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) make a decision to grant permission to concentrate if the concentration subject to control does not involve circumstances specified in subsection 22 (2) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teeb t&auml;iendava menetluse alustamise otsuse, et selgitada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 22 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud asjaolude olemasolu v&otilde;i puudumine kontrollitava koondumise puhul; </eesti>
<inglise>2) make a decision to initiate supplementary proceedings in order to ascertain whether the concentration subject to control does or does not involve circumstances specified in subsection 22 (2) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) saadab kirjaliku teate koondumise teate esitajale, kui tegemist ei ole koondumisega k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 19 l&otilde;ike 1 v&otilde;i 2 t&auml;henduses v&otilde;i koondumist ei kontrollita &sect; 21 kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>3) send a written notice to the person who submitted the notice of concentration if the concentration does not fall within the scope of subsection 19 (1) or (2) of this Act or is not subject to control pursuant to &sect; 21 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&auml;iendava menetluse k&auml;igus teeb Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja nelja kuu jooksul &uuml;he j&auml;rgmistest otsustest: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the course of supplementary proceedings, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall make one of the following decisions within four months: </inglise>
<eesti>1) annab koondumiseks loa; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to grant permission to concentrate; </inglise>
<eesti>2) keelab koondumise; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to prohibit the concentration; </inglise>
<eesti>3) l&otilde;petab menetluse, kui koondumise osalised loobuvad koondumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to terminate the proceedings if the parties to the concentration decide not to concentrate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;ltimaks turguvalitseva seisundi tekkimise v&otilde;i tugevnemisega seotud konkurentsi kahjustamist, v&otilde;ib Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja, l&auml;htudes koondumise osaliste ettepanekust, koondumiseks loa andmise otsuses kehtestada koondumise osalistele koondumisega otseselt seotud tingimused ja panna kohustused. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In order to avoid restriction of competition through creation or strengthening of a dominant position, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may, by a decision to grant permission to concentrate, attach conditions and obligations directly related to the concentration for the parties to the concentration, taking into account the proposals of the parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Koondumine on lubatud, kui Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja ei ole k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaegade jooksul teinud &uuml;hte nendes l&otilde;igetes s&auml;testatud otsustest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A concentration is permitted if the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy has not made one of the decisions provided for in subsection (1) and (2) of this section within the term specified in the same subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Koondumise osalised ei tohi enne k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud otsuse tegemist teha toiminguid koondumise teostamiseks ega teha midagi, mis v&otilde;ib takistada koondumist keelava otsuse t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Before adoption of a decision specified in subsection (2) of this section, the parties to the concentration shall not perform any acts directed at giving effect to the concentration or do anything that would hinder execution of a decision prohibiting the concentration. </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;ik nimetatud toimingud on kehtetud loa saamiseni, v&auml;lja arvatud juhul, kui koondumine on lubatud vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikele 4. </eesti>
<inglise>Unless concentration is permitted pursuant to subsection (4) of this section, all such acts are void until permission is obtained. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja on m&auml;&auml;ranud t&auml;htaja koondumise teates puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamiseks, hakkab k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaeg kulgema alates puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy sets a term for elimination of the deficiencies contained in a notice of concentration, the terms provided for in subsection (1) and (2) of this section begin to run as of the elimination of the deficiencies. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui koondumise osalised ei esita Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul vajalikku teavet v&otilde;i materjale, peatub k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaegade kulgemine teabe v&otilde;i materjalide esitamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If the parties to a concentration fail to submit the necessary information or materials within the term set by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy, the running of the terms provided for in subsections (1) and (2) of this section shall be suspended until the information or materials is submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Koondumise osalistel ja nende esindajatel on &otilde;igus tutvuda k&otilde;igi koondumise kohta kogutud materjalidega, v&auml;lja arvatud teise ettev&otilde;tja &auml;risaladus ja Konkurentsiameti sisesed dokumendid. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) The parties to a concentration and their representatives have the right to examine all materials collected on the concentration, except for the business secrets of other undertakings and the internal documents of the Competition Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Koondumise teate saamise, k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igete 1 ja 2 alusel tehtud otsuste ning l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 3 alusel saadetud kirjaliku teate kohta avaldab Konkurentsiamet teadaande v&auml;ljaandes Ametlikud Teadaanded. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) The Competition Board shall publish a notice concerning receipt of a notice of concentration, a decision made on the basis of subsection (1) or (2) of this section or a written notice sent on the basis of clause (1) 3) of this section in the official publication Ametlikud Teadaanded. </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Asjast huvitatud kolmandatel isikutel on &otilde;igus seitsme kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 9 nimetatud koondumise teate saamise kohta teadaande avaldamisest esitada Konkurentsiametile oma arvamus ja vastuv&auml;ited. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) Interested third parties have the right to submit opinions and objections to the Competition Board within seven calendar days as of publication of a notice concerning receipt of a notice of concentration specified in subsection (9) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 28. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;rakuulamine </eesti>
<inglise>Hearings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui Konkurentsiamet leiab, et menetletava koondumise puhul esinevad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 22 l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud asjaolud, teavitatakse nendest kirjalikult koondumise teate esitanud isikut. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the Competition Board finds that a concentration subject to proceedings involves the circumstances specified in subsection 22 (2) of this Act, the person who submitted the notice of concentration shall be notified of such circumstances in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Vajaduse korral v&otilde;ib l&auml;bi viia koondumise osaliste &auml;rakuulamise Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja poolt etten&auml;htud p&auml;eval ja kohas, millest teavitatakse &auml;rakuulamisele kutsutavat isikut kirjalikult mitte v&auml;hem kui 10 kalendrip&auml;eva enne &auml;rakuulamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If necessary, an oral hearing of the parties to a concentration may be held at a time and place specified by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy, and the persons to be heard shall be notified of the hearing in writing not less than ten calendar days before the hearing. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;rakuulamisele kutsutud isiku kirjaliku p&otilde;hjendatud taotluse alusel v&otilde;ib Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaega v&otilde;i kohta muuta. </eesti>
<inglise>On the basis of a reasoned written request of a person summoned to a hearing, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may change the term or the place of the hearing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 29. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 29. </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumise kehtetus </eesti>
<inglise>Nullity of concentration </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib teha otsuse koondumiseks loa andmise otsuse kehtetuks tunnistamise kohta, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may decide to revoke a decision to grant permission to concentrate if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koondumise osalised on esitanud valeandmeid v&otilde;i eksitavat v&otilde;i mittet&auml;ielikku teavet, mis oli otsuse tegemisel m&auml;&auml;rav; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the parties to the concentration submitted false, misleading or incomplete information which was a determining factor for the decision; </inglise>
<eesti>2) koondumisel on rikutud k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i koondumiseks loa andmise otsuses m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaegu v&otilde;i muid tingimusi v&otilde;i kohustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the concentration was effected in violation of a term or other condition or obligation specified in this Act or the decision to grant permission to concentrate. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Koondumise loa kehtetuks tunnistamine ei v&otilde;ta koondumise osalistelt &otilde;igust taotleda koondumiseks uut luba. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Revocation of permission to concentrate does not deprive the parties to the concentration of the right to apply for new permission to concentrate. </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi </eesti>
<inglise>State Aid </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 30. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 30. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;lds&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>General Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiabi on riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuse (edaspidi riigiabi andja) poolt v&otilde;i nende vahenditest otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik missugusel kujul antav soodustus, mis moonutab v&otilde;i v&otilde;ib moonutada konkurentsi, soodustades m&otilde;nda ettev&otilde;tjat v&otilde;i mingite kaupade tootmist v&otilde;i m&uuml;&uuml;ki. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State aid is an advantage granted directly or indirectly in any form whatsoever by the state or a local government (hereinafter grantor of state aid) or from their resources which distorts or threatens to distort competition by favouring certain undertakings or the production or sale of certain goods. </inglise>
<eesti>Selleks v&otilde;ib olla rahaline abi, maksuv&otilde;lgade tasumise ajatamine, v&otilde;lgade kustutamine, laenude andmine soodsamatel tingimustel kui tavaliselt teistele ettev&otilde;tjatele ja muus vormis antud abi. </eesti>
<inglise>Such aid may be financial aid, postponement of the payment of tax arrears, debt write-offs and the grant of loans under more favourable terms than usually granted to other undertakings, and other forms of aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigiabi andjana k&auml;sitatakse ka: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following shall also be deemed to be grantors of state aid: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sihtasutust, kes kasutab otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuse vahendeid; </eesti>
<inglise>1) foundations which directly or indirectly use the resources of the state or a local government; </inglise>
<eesti>2) mittetulundus&uuml;hingut, kes kasutab otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuse vahendeid; </eesti>
<inglise>2) non-profit associations which directly or indirectly use the resources of the state or a local government; </inglise>
<eesti>3) avalik-&otilde;iguslikku juriidilist isikut, kes kasutab otseselt v&otilde;i kaudselt riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuse vahendeid; </eesti>
<inglise>3) legal persons in public law which directly or indirectly use the resources of the state or a local government; </inglise>
<eesti>4) &auml;ri&uuml;hingut, milles riik, kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksus v&otilde;i muu avalik-&otilde;iguslik juriidiline isik omab &uuml;le poole osa- v&otilde;i aktsiakapitalist v&otilde;i &uuml;le poole aktsiate v&otilde;i osadega esindatud h&auml;&auml;ltest; </eesti>
<inglise>4) companies in which the state, a local government or any other legal person in public law holds more than one-half of the share capital or votes represented by shares; </inglise>
<eesti>5) k&auml;esoleva l&otilde;ike punktis 4 nimetatud &auml;ri&uuml;hinguga &uuml;hte kontserni kuuluvat &auml;ri&uuml;hingut. </eesti>
<inglise>5) companies belonging to the same group as a company specified in clause 4) of this subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esolev seadus ei anna &otilde;igust saada riigiabi, vaid s&auml;testab riigiabi andja &otilde;iguse anda abi ettev&otilde;tjale juhul, kui j&auml;rgitakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatut. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) This Act does not grant the right to receive state aid but provides for the right of a grantor of state aid to grant state aid to an undertaking if the provisions of this Act are complied with. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigiabiks ei loeta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud isiku sellist tegevust, kus ta k&auml;itub nii, nagu k&auml;ituks tavaliselt turumajanduse tingimustes m&otilde;istlikult tegutsev ettev&otilde;tja. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Activities of a person specified in subsection (2) of this section are not deemed to be state aid in cases where the person operates as a rational undertaking would usually operate in a market economy. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva peat&uuml;ki s&auml;tteid ei kohaldata Euroopa &Uuml;henduste ja nende liikmesriikide ning Eesti Vabariigi vahelise assotsieerumislepingu (Euroopa lepingu) (RT II 1995, 22-27, 120) artikli 63 l&otilde;ikes 5 etten&auml;htud toodete tootmise, t&ouml;&ouml;tlemise ja turustamisega tegelevale ettev&otilde;tjale riigiabina antavale abile. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The provisions of this Chapter do not apply to aid granted as state aid to undertakings engaged in the production, processing or marketing of goods prescribed in Article 63 (5) of the Europe Agreement establishing an association between the European Communities and their Member States, of the one part, and the Republic of Estonia, of the other part (RT II 1995, 22-27, 120). </inglise>
<eesti>Nimetatud abi andmise tingimused ja kord s&auml;testatakse eraldi seadustega. </eesti>
<inglise>The conditions and procedure for granting such aid shall be provided by separate Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 31. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 31. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi andmise &uuml;ld- ja eritingimused </eesti>
<inglise>General and special conditions for granting state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Anda v&otilde;ib ainult &uuml;ldiste huvidega kokkusobivat riigiabi, mis vastab k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatule ja k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 6 alusel kehtestatud eritingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State aid may be granted only if it is compatible with the public interest and complies with the provisions of this Act and the special conditions established on the basis of subsection (6) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Uuml;ldiste huvidega sobib kokku j&auml;rgmist t&uuml;&uuml;pi riigiabi: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The following types of state aid are deemed to be compatible with the public interest: </inglise>
<eesti>1) sotsiaalse iseloomuga riigiabi tingimusel, et sellise riigiabi andmisega ei kaasne toodete p&auml;ritolul p&otilde;hinevat diskrimineerimist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) state aid having a social character provided that such aid is granted without discrimination related to the origin of the goods concerned; </inglise>
<eesti>2) riigiabi loodus&otilde;nnetuste ja muude erakorraliste s&uuml;ndmuste t&otilde;ttu tekkinud kahjude heastamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) state aid to make good the damage caused by natural disasters or other exceptional occurrences. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatule v&otilde;ib &uuml;ldiste huvidega kokkusobivaks pidada riigiabi: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) In addition to the provisions of subsection (2) of this section, the following may be considered to be compatible with the public interest: </inglise>
<eesti>1) majandusliku arengu edendamiseks piirkondades, kus elatustase on v&auml;ga madal v&otilde;i kus t&ouml;&ouml;puudus on v&auml;ga k&otilde;rge; </eesti>
<inglise>1) state aid to promote the economic development of areas where the standard of living is very low or where there is serious unemployment; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &uuml;leeuroopalist huvi pakkuva projekti elluviimiseks v&otilde;i t&otilde;sise majandush&auml;ire k&otilde;rvaldamiseks Eestis; </eesti>
<inglise>2) state aid to promote the execution of a project of common European interest or to remedy a serious disturbance in the Estonian economy; </inglise>
<eesti>3) teatud majandustegevuse v&otilde;i teatud majanduspiirkondade arengu soodustamiseks, kui selline abi ei m&otilde;ju majandustingimustele negatiivselt ulatuses, mis on vastuolus &uuml;ldiste huvidega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) state aid to facilitate the development of certain economic activities or economic areas, where such aid does not adversely affect trading conditions to an extent contrary to the public interest; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kultuuri edendamiseks ja kultuurip&auml;randi s&auml;ilitamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>4) state aid to promote culture and heritage conservation. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Riigiabi antakse kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud perioodiks ja ulatuses, mis on vajalik k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud eesm&auml;rgi saavutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) State aid shall be granted for a specified term and to the extent necessary to achieve an objective specified in subsection (2) or (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>Sellise riigiabi andmine tuleb l&otilde;petada, kui see ei vasta enam k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 s&auml;testatud &uuml;ldtingimusele v&otilde;i l&otilde;ike 6 alusel kehtestatud eritingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>The grant of such state aid shall be terminated if it no longer complies with the general conditions provided in subsections (2) and (3) of this section or the special conditions established on the basis of subsection (6) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Riigiabi kogusuuruse arvutamisel arvestatakse ka Euroopa &Uuml;henduste ja nende liikmesriikide vahenditest ettev&otilde;tjale antud riigiabi, kui k&auml;esolevas seaduses v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 6 alusel kehtestatud eritingimustes ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In calculating the total amount of state aid, state aid granted to an undertaking out of the resources of the European Communities or the Member States thereof shall also be taken into account unless otherwise provided by this Act or the special conditions established on the basis of subsection (6) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Riigiabi andmise eritingimused ja nendega seotud m&otilde;isted kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus valdkonniti, l&auml;htudes Euroopa lepingu artikli 63 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatust. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The special conditions for granting state aid and the related definitions shall be established by the Government of the Republic separately for each area of activity, taking into account the provisions of subsection 63 (2) of the Europe Agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 32. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 32. </inglise>
<eesti>Eksporditegevusega seotud riigiabi ja abi impordi asendamiseks </eesti>
<inglise>State aid relating to export activities and aid to substitute imports </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eksporditegevusega seotud riigiabi (edaspidi ekspordiabi) ja abi impordi asendamiseks ei ole kokkusobiv &uuml;ldiste huvidega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State aid relating to export activities (hereinafter export aid) and aid to substitute imports are not compatible with the public interest. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ekspordiabi on abi, mis on otseselt seotud eksporditavate kaupade kogustega, turustusv&otilde;rgu sisseseadmise ja k&auml;igushoidmisega v&otilde;i muude eksporditegevusega seotud jooksvate kuludega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Export aid is any aid directly linked to the quantities of goods exported, to the establishment and operation of a distribution network or to any other current expenditure linked to the export activity. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Abi impordi asendamiseks on abi, mida antakse ettev&otilde;tjale imporditud kaupade asemel kodumaisete kaupade kasutamise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Aid to substitute imports is aid granted to an undertaking for using domestic goods instead of imported goods. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Ekspordiabina ei k&auml;sitata abi, mida antakse ettev&otilde;tjale osalemiseks kaubandusmessidel ning uuringuteks v&otilde;i konsultatsiooniteenusteks, mis on vajalikud uue v&otilde;i olemasoleva toote m&uuml;&uuml;gilelaskmiseks uuel turul. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Aid granted to an undertaking for participating in trade fairs or for studies or consultancy services needed for the launch of a new or existing product in a new market is not deemed to be export aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) &Uuml;ldiste huvidega v&otilde;ib kokkusobivaks pidada ekspordi garanteerimist ja krediteerimist, kui see ei ole vastuolus Euroopa lepingu v&otilde;i m&otilde;ne muu v&auml;lislepinguga. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Export guarantees and credits may be deemed to be compatible with the public interest if the guarantees or credits do not contradict the Europe Agreement or any other international agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 33. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 33. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega abi </eesti>
<inglise>De minimis aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Abi, mis ei &uuml;leta ettev&otilde;tja kohta 1,5 miljonit krooni kolme j&auml;rjestikuse aasta jooksul, on v&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Aid granted during three consecutive years in an amount not exceeding 1.5 million kroons per undertaking is deemed to be de minimis aid. </inglise>
<eesti>V&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega abi loetakse &uuml;ldiste huvidega kokkusobivaks. </eesti>
<inglise>De minimis aid is deemed to be compatible with the public interest. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatut ei kohaldata transpordile antava riigiabi, ekspordiabi ja impordi asendamiseks antava abi puhul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The provisions of subsection (1) of this section do not apply in the case of state aid granted to transport, export aid or aid to substitute imports. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) V&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega abi andmiseks ei ole vaja taotleda k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 34 s&auml;testatud riigiabi andmise luba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) It is not necessary to apply for permission to grant state aid, as provided in &sect; 34 of this Act, in order to grant de minimis aid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 34. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 34. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi andmise luba </eesti>
<inglise>Permission to grant state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiabi v&otilde;ib anda ainult rahandusministri eelneval kirjalikul loal ning riigiabi andmist ei alustata enne, kui rahandusminister on andnud riigiabi andmise loa v&otilde;i kui vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ikele 3 loetakse riigiabi rahandusministri poolt lubatuks v&otilde;i kui Vabariigi Valitsus on vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 48 andnud riigiabi andmise loa. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) State aid shall be granted only with the prior written permission of the Minister of Finance and the grant of state aid shall not commence before the Minister of Finance has granted permission to grant state aid or deemed the state aid to be permitted pursuant to subsection 36 (3) of this Act or before the Government of the Republic has granted permission to grant state aid pursuant to &sect; 48 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigiabi andmise loa taotlus (edaspidi loa taotlus) esitatakse rahandusministrile koos kogu vajaliku teabega, arvestades k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud menetlemise t&auml;htaegu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Applications for permission to grant state aid (hereinafter applications for permission) shall be submitted to the Minister of Finance together with the necessary information taking into account the terms in the proceedings provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa taotluse vormi(d) ja nende t&auml;itmise juhendi(d) kehtestab rahandusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>The format(s) of applications for permission and the instructions for completing the applications shall be established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahandusminister teeb riigiabi andmise loa taotluse kohta otsuse vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 36 v&otilde;i 38. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A decision concerning an application for permission to grant state aid shall be made by the Minister of Finance pursuant to &sect; 36 or 38 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse teeb rahandusminister oma k&auml;skkirjaga, viidates k&auml;esoleva seaduse vastavale s&auml;ttele. </eesti>
<inglise>The decision shall be adopted by a directive of the Minister of Finance which shall contain a reference to the relevant provision of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsusest teavitatakse viivitamata kirjalikult loa taotlejat. </eesti>
<inglise>The applicant for permission shall be immediately notified of the decision in writing. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 35. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 35. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi programm ja individuaalne riigiabi </eesti>
<inglise>State aid scheme and individual state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiabi andja v&otilde;ib riigiabi andmise luba taotleda nii riigiabi programmi (edaspidi abiprogramm) kui individuaalse riigiabi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A grantor of state aid may apply for permission to grant state aid both in the case of a state aid scheme (hereinafter aid scheme) and in the case of individual state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Abiprogrammi aluseks on igasugune &otilde;igusakt v&otilde;i leping, millest tuleneb v&otilde;imalus anda riigiabi &otilde;igusaktis v&otilde;i lepingus eelnevalt kindlaks m&auml;&auml;ratlemata ettev&otilde;tjatele &uuml;he eesm&auml;rgi v&otilde;i sarnaste eesm&auml;rkide saavutamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A state aid scheme is based on any legal act or contract which provides for the possibility for state aid to be granted to undertakings not previously defined by the act or contract in order to promote achievement of one and the same objective or several similar objectives. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Individuaalne riigiabi on riigiabi, mida ei anta abiprogrammi raames, v&otilde;i abiprogrammi raames antav riigiabi, mille kohta tuleb taotleda eraldi rahandusministri luba. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Individual state aid is state aid which is not granted on the basis of an aid scheme, or state aid which is granted on the basis of an aid scheme and for which separate permission must be applied for from the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 36. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi andmise loa taotluse menetlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings concerning applications for permission to grant state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusminister vaatab talle esitatud loa taotluse l&auml;bi ja teeb &uuml;he j&auml;rgmistest otsustest: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Finance shall examine the applications for permission submitted to him or her and make one of the following decisions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tagastab taotluse, kui taotluses esitatu ei ole riigiabi k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 l&otilde;ike 1 t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to return the application if the measures set out in the application do not constitute state aid within the meaning of subsection 30 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>2) annab riigiabi andmise loa, kui taotluses esitatud riigiabi on kokkusobiv &uuml;ldiste huvidega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to grant permission to grant state aid if the state aid specified in the application is compatible with the public interest; </inglise>
<eesti>3) algatab riigiabi andmise loa taotluse kohta t&auml;iendava menetluse, kui tal on alust kahelda riigiabi kokkusobivuses &uuml;ldiste huvidega. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to initiate supplementary proceedings concerning the application for permission to grant state aid if doubts are raised as to the compatibility of the state aid with the public interest. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister teeb &uuml;he k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud otsustest kahe kuu jooksul p&auml;rast riigiabi loa taotleja v&otilde;i riigiabi saaja poolt k&otilde;igi vajalike andmete esitamist v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 37 l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud teate esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Finance shall make one of the decisions provided for in subsection (1) of this section within two months after all the necessary information is submitted by the person applying for permission to grant state aid or the beneficiary of the state aid or a notice specified in subsection 37 (3) of this Act is received. </inglise>
<eesti>Seda t&auml;htaega v&otilde;ib muuta rahandusministri ja loa taotleja omavahelisel kirjalikul kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>The above term may be altered with the mutual written consent of the Minister of Finance and the applicant for permission. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui loa taotleja ei ole k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul saanud kirjalikku teadet rahandusministri poolt l&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt tehtud otsuse kohta, teavitab ta sellest rahandusministrit. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If, within the term provided for in subsection (2) of this section, an applicant for permission has not received a written notice concerning a decision made by the Minister of Finance pursuant to subsection (1), the person shall notify the Minister of Finance thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui rahandusminister eeltoodud teate k&auml;ttesaamisele j&auml;rgneva 15 t&ouml;&ouml;p&auml;eva jooksul ei ole loa taotlejale teatanud &uuml;hest k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 kohaselt tehtud otsusest, loetakse riigiabi rahandusministri poolt lubatuks. </eesti>
<inglise>If, within fifteen working days after receipt of the abovementioned notice, the Minister of Finance has not notified the applicant for permission of a decision made pursuant to subsection (1) of this section, the grant of state aid is deemed to be permitted by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 37. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 37. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe n&otilde;udmine </eesti>
<inglise>Requests for information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusministril on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda riigiabi andmise loa taotluse menetluse l&auml;biviimiseks vajalikke andmeid loa taotlejalt, abi saajalt ja kolmandatelt isikutelt kahe kuu jooksul riigiabi andmise loa taotluse v&otilde;i mis tahes n&otilde;utud lisateabe k&auml;ttesaamise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Finance has the right to request an applicant for permission to grant state aid, the beneficiary and third parties to submit information necessary for the proceedings concerning the application within two months after the date of receipt of the application or any additional information requested. </inglise>
<eesti>Seda t&auml;htaega muudetakse vastavalt sellele, kuidas on muudetud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>The above term shall be altered according to how the term provided for in subsection 36 (2) of this Act is altered. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui loa taotleja vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 34 l&otilde;ikele 2 esitatud riigiabi andmise loa taotluses esitatav teave on eba&otilde;ige, mittet&auml;ielik v&otilde;i eksitav v&otilde;i taotluse l&auml;bivaatamiseks on vaja t&auml;iendavaid andmeid, teavitatakse sellest loa taotlejat, abi saajat v&otilde;i kolmandaid isikuid kirjalikult, n&otilde;udes m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks puuduste k&otilde;rvaldamist v&otilde;i andmete esitamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If information set out in an application submitted pursuant to subsection 34 (2) of this Act by an applicant for permission to grant state aid is incorrect, incomplete or misleading or if additional information is necessary in order to examine the application, the applicant for permission, the beneficiary of the aid or third parties shall be notified thereof in writing and requested to eliminate the deficiencies or submit the information within a specified term. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Loa taotlus loetakse mitteesitatuks, kui k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud t&auml;htp&auml;evaks ei ole puudused k&otilde;rvaldatud v&otilde;i loa taotleja ei ole esitanud kogu n&otilde;utud teavet v&otilde;i ta ei ole selleks t&auml;htajaks teatanud, et n&otilde;utud t&auml;iendav teave ei ole k&auml;ttesaadav v&otilde;i see on juba esitatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An application for permission shall be deemed not to have been submitted if the deficiencies have not been eliminated or the applicant has not submitted all the information requested by the end of the term specified in subsection (2) of this section or if the applicant has not given notice by then that the additional information requested is not available or has already been submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe mittek&auml;ttesaadavus peab olema p&otilde;hjendatud. </eesti>
<inglise>The unavailability of information shall be reasoned. </inglise>
<eesti>Loa taotluse mitteesitatuks lugemisest teatatakse taotlejale kirjalikult. </eesti>
<inglise>The applicant for permission shall be given written notice if the application for permission is deemed not to have been submitted. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib loa taotleja vastava taotluse alusel ning m&otilde;juvate p&otilde;hjuste olemasolu korral k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 nimetatud t&auml;htaega pikendada. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Minister of Finance may, with good reason, extend the term specified in subsection (2) of this section on the basis of a corresponding petition from the applicant for permission. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 38. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 38. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;iendava menetluse l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of supplementary proceedings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusminister l&otilde;petab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 3 alusel alustatud t&auml;iendava menetluse, tehes &uuml;he j&auml;rgmistest otsustest: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Finance shall terminate supplementary proceedings initiated on the basis of clause 36 (1) 3) of this Act by making one of the following decisions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) annab riigiabi andmise loa, kui riigiabi on kokkusobiv &uuml;ldiste huvidega; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to grant permission to grant state aid if the state aid is compatible with the public interest; </inglise>
<eesti>2) tagastab taotluse, kui ta p&auml;rast loa taotleja poolt abiprogrammis v&otilde;i individuaalse riigiabi kavas tehtud muudatusi leiab, et taotluses esitatu ei ole riigiabi k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 30 l&otilde;ike 1 t&auml;henduses; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to return the application if, after amendment of the planned aid scheme or individual state aid by the applicant, the Minister of Finance finds that the measures set out in the application do not constitute state aid within the meaning of subsection 30 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) annab riigiabi andmise loa, kui ta p&auml;rast loa taotleja poolt abiprogrammis v&otilde;i individuaalse riigiabi kavas tehtud muudatusi leiab, et riigiabi on kokkusobiv &uuml;ldiste huvidega; </eesti>
<inglise>3) to grant permission to grant state aid if, after amendment of the aid scheme or the planned individual state aid by the applicant, the Minister of Finance finds that the state aid is compatible with the public interest; </inglise>
<eesti>4) keeldub riigiabi andmise loa andmisest, kui riigiabi ei sobi kokku &uuml;ldiste huvidega. </eesti>
<inglise>4) to refuse to grant permission to grant state aid if the state aid is incompatible with the public interest. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktides 1 ja 3 s&auml;testatud otsusele lisada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 31 l&otilde;ike 6 alusel kehtestatud eritingimustele vastavaid tingimusi, mille t&auml;itmise korral v&otilde;ib abi lugeda &uuml;ldiste huvidega kokkusobivaks, ja kohustusi, mis v&otilde;imaldavad j&auml;lgida otsuse t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Finance may attach to a decision provided for in clause (1) 1) or 3) of this section conditions corresponding to the special conditions established on the basis of subsection 31 (6) of this Act subject to which an aid may be deemed compatible with the public interest and may lay down obligations to enable compliance with the decision to be monitored. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahandusminister teeb k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud otsused kuue kuu jooksul p&auml;rast k&otilde;igi vajalike andmete laekumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Finance shall make the decisions provided for in subsection (1) of this section within six months after receipt of all the necessary information. </inglise>
<eesti>Seda t&auml;htaega v&otilde;ib vajaduse korral muuta rahandusministri ja loa taotleja omavahelisel kirjalikul kokkuleppel. </eesti>
<inglise>If necessary, the above term may be altered with the mutual written consent of the Minister of Finance and the applicant for the permission. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 39. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 39. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi andmise loa taotluse tagasiv&otilde;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Withdrawal of application for permission to grant state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Loa taotleja v&otilde;ib k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 34 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud riigiabi andmise loa taotluse tagasi v&otilde;tta enne, kui rahandusminister on teinud otsuse vastavalt &sect;-le 36. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An applicant for permission to grant state aid provided for in subsection 34 (2) of this Act may withdraw the application before the Minister of Finance has made a decision pursuant to &sect; 36. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&auml;iendav menetlus on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 3 alusel juba algatatud ja loa taotleja v&otilde;tab loa taotluse tagasi enne, kui rahandusminister on teinud otsuse vastavalt &sect;-le 38, teeb rahandusminister oma k&auml;skkirjaga otsuse menetluse l&otilde;petamiseks ja loa taotluse tagastamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If supplementary proceedings have been initiated on the basis of clause 36 (1) 3) of this Act and the applicant for permission withdraws the application before the Minister of Finance makes a decision pursuant to &sect; 38, the Minister of Finance shall, by a directive, make a decision to terminate the proceedings and to return the application. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 40. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 40. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuste avaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Publication of decisions </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ike 1 punktide 2 ja 3, &sect; 38 l&otilde;ike 1 punktide 1, 3 ja 4, &sect; 39 l&otilde;ike 2 ning &sect; 43 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel tehtud rahandusministri otsused avaldatakse v&auml;ljaandes Ametlikud Teadaanded. </eesti>
<inglise>Decisions made by the Minister of Finance on the basis of clause 36 (1) 2) or 3), clause 38 (1) 1), 3) or 4), subsection 39 (2) or subsection 43 (1) of this Act shall be published in the official publication Ametlikud Teadaanded. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 41. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 41. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuse t&uuml;histamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of decisions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib t&uuml;histada vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ike 1 punktile 1 v&otilde;i 2 v&otilde;i &sect; 38 l&otilde;ikele 1 tehtud otsuse, kui see p&otilde;hines menetluse k&auml;igus esitatud eba&otilde;igel teabel, mis oli otsuse tegemisel m&auml;&auml;rav. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Minister of Finance may revoke a decision made pursuant to clause 36 (1) 1) or 2) or subsection 38 (1) of this Act if the decision was based on incorrect information submitted during the proceedings which was a determining factor for the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>Enne otsuse t&uuml;histamist ja uue otsuse tegemist algatab rahandusminister t&auml;iendava menetluse vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ike 1 punktile 3. </eesti>
<inglise>Before revoking a decision and making a new decision, the Minister of Finance shall initiate supplementary proceedings pursuant to clause 36 (1) 3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui rahandusminister p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud t&auml;iendavat menetlust teeb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 38 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 4 s&auml;testatud otsuse, v&otilde;ib ta n&otilde;uda riigiabi tagastamist vastavalt &sect;-le 43. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the Minister of Finance makes a decision provided for in clause 38 (1) 4) of this Act after termination of the supplementary proceedings specified in subsection (1) of this section, he or she may demand recovery of the state aid pursuant to &sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 42. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 42. </inglise>
<eesti>Ebaseadusliku riigiabiga ja riigiabi v&auml;&auml;rkasutamisega seotud menetlus </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings concerning unlawful state aid and misuse of state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ebaseaduslik riigiabi on riigiabi, mida hakati andma p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist ning millele rahandusminister ei ole andnud luba v&otilde;i mida ei loeta lubatuks vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ikele 3 v&otilde;i mille kohta Vabariigi Valitsus vastavalt &sect;-le 48 ei ole andnud riigiabi andmise luba. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unlawful state aid is state aid which is granted after the entry into force of this Act and for which the corresponding permission has not been granted by the Minister of Finance or which is not deemed to have been permitted pursuant to subsection 36 (3) of this Act or concerning which permission to grant state aid has not been obtained from the Government of the Republic pursuant to &sect; 48 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigiabi v&auml;&auml;rkasutamine on riigiabi kasutamine eesm&auml;rgil, mis on erinev kasutusest v&otilde;i eesm&auml;rgist, mis oli nimetatud riigiabi kohta esitatud teabes, v&otilde;i k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 38 l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud tingimuste v&otilde;i kohustuste mittet&auml;itmine. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Misuse of state aid is the use of state aid for purposes other than the intended use or purpose specified in the information submitted concerning the state aid, or non-compliance with the conditions or obligations provided for in subsection 38 (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ebaseaduslikust riigiabist v&otilde;i riigiabi v&auml;&auml;rkasutamisest v&otilde;ivad rahandusministrile teatada k&otilde;ik asjast huvitatud kolmandad isikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) All interested third parties may notify the Minister of Finance of unlawful state aid or the misuse of state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui rahandusminister saab teavet v&auml;idetava ebaseadusliku riigiabi v&otilde;i riigiabi v&auml;&auml;rkasutamise kohta, teeb ta ettekirjutuse: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the Minister of Finance receives information concerning alleged unlawful state aid or alleged misuse of state aid, he or she shall issue a precept: </inglise>
<eesti>1) riigiabi andjale v&otilde;i riigiabi saajale teabe esitamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to the grantor of the state aid or the beneficiary of the state aid requiring information to be submitted within a specified term; </inglise>
<eesti>2) riigiabi andjale riigiabi andmise loa taotluse esitamiseks m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htaja jooksul; </eesti>
<inglise>2) to the grantor of the state aid requiring an application for permission to grant state aid to be submitted within a specified term; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigiabi andjale ebaseadusliku riigiabi v&otilde;i v&auml;idetavalt v&auml;&auml;rkasutatud riigiabi andmise peatamiseks, kuni ta on selle kohta teinud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 1 v&otilde;i 2 v&otilde;i &sect; 38 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud otsuse. </eesti>
<inglise>3) to the grantor of the state aid requiring suspension of the grant of unlawful state aid or alleged misused state aid until the Minister of Finance has made a decision provided for in clause 36 (1) 1) or 2) or subsection 38 (1) of this Act concerning the matter. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Ebaseadusliku riigiabiga v&otilde;i riigiabi v&auml;&auml;rkasutamisega seotud menetluse k&auml;igus teeb rahandusminister otsuse vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 36. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) In the course of proceedings concerning unlawful state aid or the misuse of state aid, the Minister of Finance shall make a decision pursuant to &sect; 36 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui riigiabi andja v&otilde;i riigiabi saaja ei t&auml;ida k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud ettekirjutust v&otilde;i ei esita n&otilde;utud lisateavet, tehakse otsus olemasoleva teabe p&otilde;hjal. </eesti>
<inglise>If a grantor of state aid or a beneficiary of state aid fails to comply with a precept provided for in subsection (4) of this section or to submit the additional information requested, the decision shall be made on the basis of the existing information. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 3 alusel algatatav t&auml;iendav menetlus l&otilde;petatakse &uuml;he &sect; 38 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud otsusega. </eesti>
<inglise>Supplementary proceedings initiated on the basis of clause 36 (1) 3) of this Act shall be terminated by making one of the decisions provided for in subsection 38 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kui rahandusminister p&auml;rast t&auml;iendavat menetlust teeb k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 38 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 4 s&auml;testatud otsuse, v&otilde;ib ta n&otilde;uda riigiabi tagastamist vastavalt &sect;-le 43. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) If the Minister of Finance makes a decision provided for in clause 38 (1) 4) of this Act after termination of supplementary proceedings, he or she may demand that the state aid is recovered pursuant to &sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 43. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 43. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi tagastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Recovery of state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 41 v&otilde;i 42 alusel l&auml;biviidud t&auml;iendavat menetlust tehakse &sect; 38 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 4 s&auml;testatud otsus, on rahandusministril &otilde;igus teha riigiabi andjale v&otilde;i riigiabi saajale ettekirjutus riigiabi andmise otsuse t&uuml;histamiseks v&otilde;i riigiabi tagastamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a decision provided for in clause 38 (1) 4) is made after supplementary proceedings conducted on the basis of &sect; 41 or 42 of this Act, the Minister of Finance has the right to issue a precept to the grantor or beneficiary of the state aid requiring revocation of the decision to grant state aid or recovery of the state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tagastamisele kuuluva riigiabi suuruse arvutamisel arvestatakse abi suurust ja kulusid enne nendelt otseste maksude mahaarvamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In calculating the amount of state aid to be recovered, the size of the aid and expenses before the deduction of direct taxes shall be taken into account. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui abi anti mitterahalises vormis, teisendatakse see v&otilde;rdse v&auml;&auml;rtusega rahaliseks toetuseks. </eesti>
<inglise>If aid was granted in a form other than monetary support, the aid shall be converted into financial support of an equal value. </inglise>
<eesti>Abi, mida anti mitmete osamaksetena, diskonteeritakse selle hetkev&auml;&auml;rtusesse. </eesti>
<inglise>Aid granted in instalments shall be discounted to the present value. </inglise>
<eesti>Diskontom&auml;&auml;raks on riigiabi viiteintress, mis kehtis ajal, kui abi tehti k&auml;ttesaadavaks. </eesti>
<inglise>The reference interest rate applicable to the state aid at the time when the aid was made available shall be used as the discount rate. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Rahandusministril on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 41 l&otilde;ikes 2 ning &sect; 42 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 nimetatud riigiabi tagastamist 10 aasta jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Minister of Finance has the right to demand recovery of state aid specified in subsections 41 (2) and 42 (1) and (2) of this Act within ten years. </inglise>
<eesti>T&auml;htaja kulgemine algab riigiabi k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemise p&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>The term begins to run as of the date when the state aid is made available. </inglise>
<eesti>Rahandusministri poolt l&auml;biviidava menetluse v&otilde;i asja kohtuliku menetluse ajaks t&auml;htaja kulgemine peatub. </eesti>
<inglise>The running of the term shall be suspended for the period during which proceedings are conducted by the Minister of Finance or the matter is heard by a court. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui riigiabi saaja ei t&auml;ida ettekirjutust riigiabi tagastamise kohta, on rahandusministril &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If a beneficiary of state aid fails to comply with a precept concerning recovery of the state aid, the Minister of Finance has the right of recourse to the courts. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 44. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 44. </inglise>
<eesti>Intressi n&otilde;udmine </eesti>
<inglise>Demand of interest </inglise>
<eesti>Rahandusministril on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda intressi iga riigiabi tagastamise juhtumi korral k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 43 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel tagastatava riigiabi summalt. </eesti>
<inglise>In each case of the recovery of state aid, the Minister of Finance has the right to demand interest to be paid on the amount of state aid recovered on the basis of subsection 43 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Sissen&otilde;utud intressid kantakse riigieelarve tuludesse. </eesti>
<inglise>The interest collected shall be transferred to the revenue of the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>Intressi arvestatakse alates riigiabi k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemise p&auml;evast, kasutades selleks abi lubamise otsusele v&otilde;i selle puudumisel riigiabi andmisele eelnenud kuu Eesti pankade poolt mittefinantssektori ettev&otilde;tjatele antavate laenude keskmist intressim&auml;&auml;ra. </eesti>
<inglise>Interest shall be calculated as of the date when the state aid was made available, using the average interest rate applied by Estonian banks to loans granted to undertakings in non-financial sectors during the month preceding the date of the decision to permit the grant of the state aid or, in the absence of such decision, the month preceding the grant of the state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 45. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 45. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettekirjutus </eesti>
<inglise>Precepts </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 42 l&otilde;ikes 4 ja &sect; 43 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud ettekirjutusse m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A precept specified in subsection 42 (4) or 43 (1) of this Act shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ettekirjutuse koostaja nimi ja ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name and position of the person preparing the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>2) ettekirjutuse tegemise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the date of issue of the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ettekirjutuse saaja nimi ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the name and address of the recipient of the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ettekirjutuse tegemise alused koos viidetega vastavate &otilde;igusaktide s&auml;tetele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the bases for issuing the precept together with references to the provisions of relevant Acts; </inglise>
<eesti>5) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 42 l&otilde;ike 4 punktis 1 s&auml;testatud juhul m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks, millist teavet n&otilde;utakse; </eesti>
<inglise>5) in the case provided for in clause 42 (4) 1) of this Act, an indication of the information requested; </inglise>
<eesti>6) ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmise t&auml;htaeg; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the term for compliance with the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>7) sunniraha summa, mida rakendatakse ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the amount of the penalty payment applied upon failure to comply with the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>8) ettekirjutuse peale edasikaebamise kord ja t&auml;htaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>8) the procedure and term for appeal against the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib ettekirjutuses ette n&auml;ha riigiabi andmise peatamisega kaasnevaid kohustuslikke toiminguid. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A precept of the Minister of Finance may prescribe obligatory acts to be performed upon suspension of the grant of the state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 46. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 46. </inglise>
<eesti>Sunniraha m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Imposition of penalty payment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusminister v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 45 s&auml;testatud ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral sunniraha f&uuml;&uuml;silistele isikutele kuni 50 000 krooni ja juriidilistele isikutele kuni 100 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In the case of failure to comply with a precept provided for in &sect; 45 of this Act, the Minister of Finance may impose a penalty payment of up to 50 000 kroons on natural persons and up to 100 000 kroons on legal persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud sunniraha v&otilde;ib ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmiseni rakendada korduvalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A penalty payment provided for in subsection (1) of this section may be imposed several times until the corresponding precept is complied with. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 47. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 47. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabikomisjon </eesti>
<inglise>State aid committee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vabariigi Valitsus moodustab riigiabikomisjoni (edaspidi komisjon), mille &uuml;lesandeks on k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 48 l&otilde;ike 1 alusel rahandusministri otsuse kehtetuks tunnistamiseks esitatud taotluse kohta ettepanekute esitamine Vabariigi Valitsusele. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Government of the Republic shall form a state aid committee (hereinafter committee) whose function is to submit proposals to the Government of the Republic concerning applications for revocation of a decision of the Minister of Finance submitted on the basis of subsection 48 (1) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Komisjoni moodustamise korra ja t&ouml;&ouml;korralduse kehtestab Vabariigi Valitsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The procedure for the formation of and the organisation of the work of the committee shall be established by the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 48. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 48. </inglise>
<eesti>Vaidlusaluse riigiabi juhtumi menetlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings concerning disputable cases of state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui rahandusminister lisab k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 38 l&otilde;ike 2 alusel oma otsusele tingimusi ja kohustusi v&otilde;i teeb &sect; 38 l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 4 s&auml;testatud otsuse, millega loa taotleja ei n&otilde;ustu, on loa taotlejal &otilde;igus p&ouml;&ouml;rduda rahandusministri otsuse kehtetuks tunnistamiseks ja uue otsuse vastuv&otilde;tmiseks komisjoni poole, kes p&auml;rast asja l&auml;bivaatamist saadab materjalid koos oma ettepanekutega Vabariigi Valitsusele otsustamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If the Minister of Finance attaches to his or her decision conditions or obligations on the basis of subsection 38 (2) of this Act or makes a decision provided for in clause 38 (1) 4) of this Act to which the applicant for permission does not consent, the applicant for permission has the right to address the committee and apply for the decision of the Minister of Finance to be revoked and a new decision to be made, and the committee shall examine the matter and send the materials together with its proposals to the Government of the Republic for a decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Komisjonile esitatakse k&otilde;ik loa taotleja, abi saaja ja kolmandate isikute poolt rahandusministrile esitatud materjalid ning rahandusministri poolt juhtumi kohta tehtud otsus. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) All materials submitted to the Minister of Finance by an applicant for permission, the beneficiary or third parties and the decision made by the Minister of Finance concerning the case shall be submitted to the committee. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Vabariigi Valitsus vaatab talle esitatud taotluse l&auml;bi ja teeb &uuml;he j&auml;rgmistest otsustest: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Government of the Republic shall examine applications submitted thereto and shall make one of the following decisions: </inglise>
<eesti>1) tunnistab kehtetuks rahandusministri otsuse ja annab oma korraldusega riigiabi andmise loa; </eesti>
<inglise>1) to revoke the decision of the Minister of Finance and to grant permission to grant state aid by an order of the Government of the Republic; </inglise>
<eesti>2) j&auml;tab talle esitatud taotluse rahuldamata. </eesti>
<inglise>2) to deny the application submitted to the Government of the Republic. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 49. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 49. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi aruandlus </eesti>
<inglise>Reporting on state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Riigiabi andmise ja kasutamise aruande vormi ning esitamise t&auml;htp&auml;eva kehtestab rahandusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The format of a report on the grant and use of state aid and the due date for the submission of the report shall be established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigiabi andja esitab riigiabi andmise ja kasutamise aruande rahandusministrile. </eesti>
<inglise>Grantors of state aid shall submit reports on the grant and use of state aid to the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Aruanne esitatakse ka v&auml;hese t&auml;htsusega riigiabi andmise ja kasutamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>Reports shall also be submitted on the grant and use of de minimis state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister koostab kalendriaasta l&otilde;ppemisest 12 kuu jooksul aruande kogu sellel aastal antud riigiabi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Within twelve months as of the end of a calendar year, the Minister of Finance shall prepare a report on all state aid granted during the given year. </inglise>
<eesti>Aruanne esitatakse kinnitamiseks Vabariigi Valitsusele. </eesti>
<inglise>The report shall be submitted to the Government of the Republic for approval. </inglise>
<eesti>7. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 7 </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;lvatu konkurents </eesti>
<inglise>Unfair Competition </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 50. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 50. </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;lvatu konkurentsi keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on unfair competition </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&otilde;lvatu konkurents on ebaaus &auml;ritegevus, heade kommete ja tavadega vastuolus olevad teod, sealhulgas: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unfair competition is taken to mean dishonest trading practices and acts which are contrary to good morals and practices, including: </inglise>
<eesti>1) eksitava teabe avaldamine, avaldamiseks esitamine, tellimine, konkurendi v&otilde;i tema kauba halvustamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) publication of misleading information, presentation or ordering of misleading information for publication, or disparagement of a competitor or the goods of the competitor; </inglise>
<eesti>2) konfidentsiaalse teabe kuritarvitamine, konkurendi t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i esindaja &auml;rakasutamine. </eesti>
<inglise>2) misuse of confidential information or of an employee or representative of a competitor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&otilde;lvatu konkurents on keelatud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Unfair competition is prohibited. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Reklaamina k&auml;sitatava eksitava, k&otilde;lvatu v&otilde;i halvustava teabe puhul rakendatakse reklaamiseaduse (RT I 1997, 52, 835; 1999, 27, 388; 30, 415; 2001, 23, 127; 50, 284) s&auml;tteid. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The provisions of the Advertising Act (RT I 1997, 52, 835; 1999, 27, 388; 30, 415; 2001, 23, 127; 50, 284) apply to misleading, offensive or denigratory information as a method of advertising. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Eksitava teabe avaldamine, avaldamiseks esitamine, tellimine, konkurendi v&otilde;i tema kauba halvustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Publication of misleading information, presentation or ordering of misleading information for publication, or disparagement of competitor or goods of competitor </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eksitav teave on ebat&otilde;esed andmed, mis v&otilde;ivad ostja tavalise t&auml;helepanelikkuse juures tekitada pakkumisest eksliku mulje v&otilde;i millega kahjustatakse v&otilde;i v&otilde;idakse kahjustada teise ettev&otilde;tja mainet v&otilde;i tema majandustegevust. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Misleading information is incorrect information which, given ordinary attention on the part of the buyer, may leave a misleading impression of an offer or which harms or may harm the reputation or economic activities of another undertaking </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Keelatud on eksitava teabe avaldamine v&otilde;i avaldamiseks esitamine v&otilde;i tellimine kas enda v&otilde;i kaubaturul osaleva teise ettev&otilde;tja, tema kauba v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;vahendi kohta, v&auml;lja arvatud teabe avaldamine, kui avaldajalt on sellise teabe avaldamine tellitud v&otilde;i avaldaja ei vastuta teiste poolt temale esitatud teabe &otilde;igsuse eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Publication, or presentation or ordering for publication, of misleading information concerning either oneself or another undertaking participating in a goods market or concerning the goods or work equipment of such undertaking is prohibited, except in cases where publication of such information has been ordered from the publisher of the information or the publisher is not responsible for the correctness of the information presented thereto. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud andmete all m&otilde;istetakse eelk&otilde;ige teavet pakutavate kaupade p&auml;ritolu, omaduste, valmistamisviisi, hankimisviisi v&otilde;i -allikate, hinna, tariifi, allahindluse, auhindamise, m&uuml;&uuml;gi p&otilde;hjuste ja varude suuruse ning ettev&otilde;tja ees&otilde;iguste, finantsseisundi ja muude omaduste kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Information specified in subsection (1) of this section primarily refers to information concerning the origin, qualities, method of production, means or sources of supply, prices, tariffs, discounts, awarding as a prize, reasons for sale and the size of the stock of the goods offered, as well as the preferential rights, financial status and other qualities of the undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 52. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 52. </inglise>
<eesti>Konfidentsiaalse teabe kuritarvitamine, teise ettev&otilde;tja t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i esindaja &auml;rakasutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Misuse of confidential information or of employee or representative of another undertaking </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konfidentsiaalse teabe kuritarvitamine on konkurendi konfidentsiaalse teabe kasutamine, kui vastavad andmed on saadud seadusevastaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Misuse of confidential information is the use of confidential information regarding a competitor where the corresponding information was obtained illegally. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurendi t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i esindaja &auml;rakasutamine on tema m&otilde;jutamine tegutsema m&otilde;jutaja v&otilde;i kolmanda isiku huvides. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Misuse of an employee or representative of a competitor is the exertion of influence on him or her to act in the interests of the influencing party or a third party. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 53. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 53. </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;lvatu konkurentsi tuvastamine </eesti>
<inglise>Ascertainment of unfair competition </inglise>
<eesti>K&otilde;lvatu konkurents v&otilde;i selle puudumine tuvastatakse poolte vaidluses tsiviilkohtumenetluse korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The existence or absence of unfair competition shall be ascertained in a dispute between parties held pursuant to civil procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>8. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 8 </inglise>
<eesti>Riiklik j&auml;relevalve </eesti>
<inglise>State Supervision </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 54. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 54. </inglise>
<eesti>Riikliku j&auml;relevalve korraldus </eesti>
<inglise>Organisation of state supervision </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiamet teostab riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;itmise &uuml;le, v&auml;lja arvatud 6. ja 7. peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatu t&auml;itmise &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Competition Board shall exercise state supervision over implementation of this Act, except implementation of the provisions of Chapters 6 and 7. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Rahandusminister teostab riiklikku j&auml;relevalvet 6. peat&uuml;kis s&auml;testatu t&auml;itmise &uuml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Minister of Finance shall exercise state supervision over implementation of the provisions of Chapter 6. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 55. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 55. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti p&auml;devus </eesti>
<inglise>Competence of Competition Board </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiamet on p&auml;dev teostama k&otilde;iki k&auml;esoleva seaduse alusel temale pandud toiminguid ja v&otilde;tma tarvitusele meetmeid konkurentsi kaitsmiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Competition Board is competent to perform all acts assigned to it by this Act and to take measures to protect competition. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiamet anal&uuml;&uuml;sib konkurentsiolukorda, kavandab konkurentsi soodustavaid meetmeid, annab soovitusi konkurentsiolukorra parandamiseks ja teeb ettepanekuid &otilde;igusaktide vastuv&otilde;tmiseks v&otilde;i muutmiseks ning arendab koost&ouml;&ouml;d teiste riikide ja riikide &uuml;henduste konkurentsialase j&auml;relevalve asutustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Competition Board shall analyse the competitive situation, propose measures to promote competition, make recommendations to improve the competitive situation, make proposals for legislation to be passed or amended, and develop co-operation with the competition supervisory authorities of other states and associations of states. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 56. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 56. </inglise>
<eesti>Koost&ouml;&ouml; Euroopa Komisjoniga </eesti>
<inglise>Co-operation with European Commission </inglise>
<eesti>Vastavalt Euroopa &Uuml;henduste ja nende liikmesriikide ning Eesti Vabariigi vahelisele assotsieerumislepingule (Euroopa leping) ja Euroopa &Uuml;henduste ja nende liikmesriikide ning Eesti Vabariigi vahelise assotsiatsioonin&otilde;ukogu otsusele nr 1/99 Euroopa &Uuml;henduste ja nende liikmesriikide ning Eesti Vabariigi vahelise assotsieerumislepingu artikli 63 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti i, l&otilde;ike 1 punkti ii ja l&otilde;ike 2 rakendamiseks vajalike eeskirjade vastuv&otilde;tmise kohta (RT II 1999, 15, 94) toimub Euroopa Komisjoni ja Konkurentsiameti koost&ouml;&ouml; nende eeskirjade artiklis 1 s&auml;testatud &uuml;ldp&otilde;him&otilde;tte kohaselt. </eesti>
<inglise>Pursuant to the Europe Agreement establishing an association between the European Communities and their Member States, of the one part, and the Republic of Estonia, of the other part and decision No. 1/99 of the Association Council between the European Communities and their Member States, of the one part, and the Republic of Estonia, of the other part adopting the necessary rules for the implementation of Article 63 (1) i), (1) ii) and (2) of the Europe Agreement establishing an association between the European Communities and their Member States, of the one part, and the Republic of Estonia, of the other part (RT II 1999, 15, 94), co-operation between the European Commission and the Competition Board shall be effected pursuant to the general principles provided for in Article 1 of the above rules. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 57. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 57. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda teavet </eesti>
<inglise>Right of Competition Board to request information </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda k&otilde;igilt f&uuml;&uuml;silistelt ja juriidilistelt isikutelt ning nende esindajatelt, samuti riigiasutustelt ja kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksustelt ning nende ametiisikutelt teavet: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Competition Board has the right to request all natural and legal persons and the representatives thereof and all state agencies and local governments and the officials thereof to submit information necessary for: </inglise>
<eesti>1) konkurentsiolukorra anal&uuml;&uuml;simiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) analysing the competitive situation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kaubaturu piiritlemiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>2) defining a goods market; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse kontrollimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>3) inspecting an agreement, activity or decision; </inglise>
<eesti>4) erandi andmise otsustamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>4) deciding on the grant of exemptions; </inglise>
<eesti>5) turguvalitsevat seisundit omava ettev&otilde;tja tegevuse kontrollimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>5) monitoring the activities of an undertaking in a dominant position; </inglise>
<eesti>6) koondumise kontrollimiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>6) monitoring a concentration; </inglise>
<eesti>7) menetlemise alustamise otsustamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>7) deciding on initiation of a proceeding; </inglise>
<eesti>8) seaduse rikkumise v&otilde;i v&otilde;imaliku rikkumise asja menetlemiseks; </eesti>
<inglise>8) conducting proceedings concerning violations or possible violations of law; </inglise>
<eesti>9) k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;itmise &uuml;le muu j&auml;relevalve teostamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>9) exercising other supervision over the implementation of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud teavet n&otilde;utakse kirjalikult, kusjuures nimetatakse &auml;ra taotluse eesm&auml;rk ja &otilde;iguslik alus ning viidatakse sanktsioonidele teabe esitamata j&auml;tmise ning mittet&auml;ieliku, eba&otilde;ige ja eksitava teabe esitamise eest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The information provided for in subsection (1) of this section shall be requested in writing, whereupon the purpose of and the legal basis for the request shall be specified and the sanctions for failure to provide information and for provision of incomplete, incorrect or misleading information shall be referred to. </inglise>
<eesti>Teabe esitamise t&auml;htajaks m&auml;&auml;ratakse mitte v&auml;hem kui 10 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>The term for submission of the information shall be not less than ten calendar days. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus f&uuml;&uuml;silist isikut, sealhulgas juriidilise isiku v&otilde;i juriidiliseks isikuks mitteoleva &uuml;henduse esindajat v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajat v&otilde;i riigiasutuse v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuse ametiisikut v&otilde;i nende esindajaid, kutsuda Konkurentsiametisse seletusi andma v&otilde;i v&otilde;tta nendelt seletusi kohapeal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Competition Board has the right to request natural persons, including representatives or employees of legal persons or associations which are not legal persons and officials or representatives of state agencies or local governments, to provide explanations at the Competition Board or on site. </inglise>
<eesti>Seletused vormistatakse kirjalikult ning iga seletuse lehek&uuml;lg allkirjastatakse seletuse v&otilde;tja ja seletuse andja poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>Explanations shall be prepared in writing and the person requesting an explanation and the person providing the explanation shall sign each page of the explanation. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui seletuse andja keeldub seletusele alla kirjutamast, tehakse seletusse kanne seletusele allakirjutamisest keeldumise ja allakirjutamisest keeldumise motiivide kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>If a person providing an explanation refuses to sign the explanation, an entry indicating refusal to sign the explanation and the reasons for the refusal shall be made in the explanation. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 58. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 58. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiametisse kutsumine </eesti>
<inglise>Summoning to Competition Board </inglise>
<eesti>(1) F&uuml;&uuml;siline isik, sealhulgas juriidilise isiku v&otilde;i juriidiliseks isikuks mitteoleva &uuml;henduse esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja v&otilde;i riigiasutuse v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuse ametiisik v&otilde;i nende esindajad, kutsutakse Konkurentsiametisse kutsega, milles m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Natural persons, including representatives or employees of legal persons or associations which are not legal persons and officials or representatives of state agencies or local governments, shall be summoned to the Competition Board by a summons which sets out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kutsutava isiku nimi v&otilde;i nimetus; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the name or official title of the person summoned; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kutsumise p&otilde;hjus ja &otilde;iguslik alus; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the reason and legal basis for summoning the person; </inglise>
<eesti>3) alustatud juhtumi korral juhtumi number; </eesti>
<inglise>3) if a case has been opened, the number of the case; </inglise>
<eesti>4) ilmumise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the place and time of appearance; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kutsutava isiku &otilde;igused, sealhulgas &otilde;igus esitada kirjalik seletus; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the rights of the person summoned, including the right to submit a written explanation; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kohustus teatada ilmumata j&auml;&auml;mise m&otilde;juvatest p&otilde;hjustest. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the obligation to give notice of good reasons for failure to appear. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kutse antakse k&auml;tte allkirja vastu v&otilde;i saadetakse posti teel v&auml;ljastusteatega (edaspidi k&auml;ttetoimetamine) ning ilmumiseks antakse kutsutud isikule v&otilde;i tema esindajale mitte v&auml;hem kui 10 kalendrip&auml;eva. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A summons shall be served against signature or sent by post with advice of delivery (hereinafter service) and the person summoned or his or her representative shall be granted a term of not less than ten calendar days to appear. </inglise>
<eesti>Poolte kokkuleppel v&otilde;ib seda t&auml;htaega muuta, samuti edastada kutse suuliselt. </eesti>
<inglise>By agreement of the parties, the term may be altered and the summons may be delivered orally. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kutsutud isikule kutse k&auml;ttetoimetamisel loetakse ka tema esindajale kutse k&auml;ttetoimetatuks, menetlusosalise esindajale kutse k&auml;ttetoimetamisel loetakse ka tema volitajale kutse k&auml;ttetoimetatuks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon service of a summons on a person, the summons shall also be deemed to have been served on the representative of the person, and upon service of a summons on the representative of a participant in a proceeding, the summons shall also be deemed to have been served on the principal. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Juriidilisele isikule loetakse kutse k&auml;ttetoimetatuks, kui see on kohale toimetatud juriidilise isiku registrisse kantud asukoha aadressil. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A summons is deemed to have been served on a legal person if it is delivered to the address of the legal person entered in the register. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui t&auml;htajaks ilmumine ei ole v&otilde;imalik, peab kutsutud isik sellest viivitamata teatama. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If it is not possible to appear within the specified term, the person summoned shall immediately give notice thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Kutsutud isiku ilmumata j&auml;&auml;mise m&otilde;juvad p&otilde;hjused on &auml;raolek, mis ei seondu menetlusest k&otilde;rvalehoidmisega, kutse k&auml;ttesaamine hilinenult v&otilde;i muu asjaolu, mille menetleja loeb m&otilde;juvaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Good reasons for the failure of a person summoned to appear are absence not related to evasion of the proceedings, belated receipt of the summons or other circumstances considered to be a good reason by the person conducting the proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 59. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 59. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda materjale </eesti>
<inglise>Right of Competition Board to request submission of materials </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda k&otilde;igilt f&uuml;&uuml;silistelt ja juriidilistelt isikutelt ning nende esindajatelt, samuti riigiasutustelt ja kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksustelt ning nende ametiisikutelt ja esindajatelt dokumentide, nende kavandite ja muude materjalide originaale v&otilde;i nende &auml;rakirju, mille vastavust originaalile kinnitab nende esitaja oma allkirjaga. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Competition Board has the right to request all natural and legal persons and the representatives thereof and all state agencies and local governments and the officials and representatives thereof to submit the originals of documents, drafts or other materials, or true copies thereof, certified by the signature of the person submitting the copies. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;rakirja esitamise korral on Konkurentsiametil &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda algdokumenti &auml;rakirja &otilde;igsuse kontrollimiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon submission of a copy, the Competition Board has the right to request submission of the original document to verify the authenticity of the copy. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Materjali &uuml;le andnud isiku v&otilde;i tema esindaja n&otilde;udel v&auml;ljastatakse talle Konkurentsiameti kinnitus vastava materjali vastuv&otilde;tmise kohta ning neil on &otilde;igus Konkurentsiametilt p&auml;rast j&auml;relevalvetoimingute l&otilde;ppu nende poolt esitatud dokumentide, kavandite ja muude materjalide originaalid tagasi saada. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) At the request of a person who submits materials or the representative of such person, the Competition Board shall issue confirmation concerning receipt of the materials and the person or the representative has the right to the return of the originals of the documents, drafts and other materials by the Competition Board after completion of the supervisory operations. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 60. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 60. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettev&otilde;tja asukoha ja tegutsemiskoha kontrollimine </eesti>
<inglise>Inspection of seat or place of business of undertaking </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja k&auml;skkirjaga volitatud Konkurentsiameti ametnikul v&otilde;i esindajal (edaspidi kontrollimist teostav isik) on &otilde;igus k&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise v&otilde;i v&otilde;imaliku rikkumise tuvastamise eesm&auml;rgil kontrollida ettev&otilde;tja asukohta ja tegutsemiskohta, sealhulgas ettev&otilde;tet, territooriumi, hoonet, ruumi ja transpordivahendit, ilma eelneva hoiatuse v&otilde;i eriloata nii t&ouml;&ouml;ajal kui tegutsemiskoha kasutamise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) In order to establish a violation or possible violation of this Act, an official or representative of the Competition Board authorised by a directive of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy (hereinafter person conducting an investigation) has the right, without prior warning or special permission, to inspect the seat and place of business of an undertaking, including the enterprises, territory, buildings, rooms and means of transport of the undertaking, both during working hours and at any time the place of business is used. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettev&otilde;tja n&otilde;usolekul v&otilde;ib tema asukohta, tegutsemiskohta v&otilde;i ettev&otilde;tet kontrollida ka muul ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>With the consent of the undertaking, the seat, place of business or enterprises of the undertaking may also be inspected at any other time. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kontrollimine toimub ettev&otilde;tja, tema esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja teadmisel ning neil on &otilde;igus viibida kontrollimise juures. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An inspection provided for in subsection (1) of this section shall be conducted with the knowledge of the undertaking, or a representative or employee thereof, and they have the right to be present during the inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kontrollitava ettev&otilde;tja asukohas v&otilde;i tegutsemiskohas esitab kontrollimist teostav isik sellele ettev&otilde;tjale, tema esindajale v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajale t&otilde;estatud &auml;rakirja v&otilde;i v&auml;ljav&otilde;tte Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusest juhtumi menetluse alustamise kohta ja Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja k&auml;skkirja kontrollimist teostava isiku volitamise kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) At the seat or place of business of an undertaking under inspection, the person conducting the inspection shall present to the undertaking, its representative or employee a certified copy or extract of the decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy concerning initiation of the proceedings with regard to the case, and a directive of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy concerning the authorisation of the person conducting the inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kontrollimist teostaval isikul on k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud kontrollimisel j&auml;rgmised &otilde;igused: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) During an inspection provided for in subsection (1) of this section, the person conducting the inspection has the right to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) &otilde;igus kontrollida viivitamata ettev&otilde;tja tegevust puudutavaid dokumente, nende kavandeid ja muid materjale ning saada neist kontrollitava ettev&otilde;tja kulul &auml;rakirju v&otilde;i koopiaid, mille originaalile vastavust kinnitab nende esitaja oma allkirjaga; </eesti>
<inglise>1) immediately examine documents relating to the activities of the undertaking, drafts thereof and other materials and to obtain, at the expense of the person under inspection, copies or transcripts thereof, the authenticity of which shall be certified by the signature of the person submitting them; </inglise>
<eesti>2) &otilde;igus kontrollida viivitamata kontrollitava ettev&otilde;tja asukohas ja tegutsemiskohas elektroonilisel kujul arvutis peetavaid andmeid ja andmebaase ning elektroonilisi andmekandjaid ning teha neist kontrollitava ettev&otilde;tja kulul v&auml;ljatr&uuml;kke ja elektroonilisi koopiaid, mille &otilde;igsust kinnitab kontrollitav isik, tema esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja oma allkirjaga v&auml;ljatr&uuml;kil v&otilde;i eraldi lehel; </eesti>
<inglise>2) immediately examine data or databases kept in electronic form on computer at the seat or place of business of the undertaking under inspection and electronic data media held at the seat or place of business and to make printouts and electronic copies thereof at the expense of the undertaking under inspection, the authenticity of which shall be certified by the signature of the person under inspection or his or her representative or employee on the printout or on a separate page; </inglise>
<eesti>3) &otilde;igus v&otilde;tta ettev&otilde;tjalt, tema esindajalt v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajalt seletusi, mis vormistatakse vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 57 l&otilde;ikele 3. </eesti>
<inglise>3) request the undertaking or a representative or employee thereof to submit explanations which shall be documented pursuant to subsection 57 (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kontrollimist teostaval isikul on kohustus koostada kontrollimise tulemuste kohta kokkuv&otilde;te. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The person conducting an inspection is required to prepare a summary of the results of the inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 nimetatud kokkuv&otilde;ttesse m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A summary specified in subsection (5) of this section shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kokkuv&otilde;tte koostamise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the time and place of preparation of the summary; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kokkuv&otilde;tte koostaja nimi ja ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and position of the person preparing the summary; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kontrollitava f&uuml;&uuml;silise isiku, tema esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja nimi ja ametikoht v&otilde;i juriidilise isiku puhul juriidilise isiku nimetus ja juriidilise isiku esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja nimi ja ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>3) in the case of a natural person under inspection, the name and position of the person or his or her representative or employee or, in the case of a legal person, the name of the legal person and the name and position of the representative or employee of the legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kontrollimise k&auml;ik; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a description of the course of the inspection; </inglise>
<eesti>5) m&auml;rge kontrollitavale ettev&otilde;tjale, tema esindajale v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajale k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 3 nimetatud otsuse &auml;rakirja v&otilde;i v&auml;ljav&otilde;tte ja k&auml;skkirja esitamise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a notation concerning presentation of a copy or extract of the decision or the directive specified in subsection (3) of this section to the undertaking under inspection or the representative or employee thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>6) loetelu kontrollitavalt ettev&otilde;tjalt, tema esindajalt v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajalt v&otilde;etud seletuste kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>6) a list of the explanations received from the undertaking under inspection or the representative or employee thereof; </inglise>
<eesti>7) kontrollimise k&auml;igus saadud materjalide loetelu; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a list of the materials obtained in the course of the inspection; </inglise>
<eesti>8) m&auml;rge t&otilde;lgi osav&otilde;tu kohta, kui t&otilde;lk osaleb; </eesti>
<inglise>8) a notation concerning the participation of an interpreter or translator if one is involved; </inglise>
<eesti>9) kontrollitava ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja m&auml;rkused kontrollimise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>9) the notes of the undertaking under inspection or the representative or employee thereof concerning the inspection; </inglise>
<eesti>10) m&auml;rge selle kohta, et kontrollitav ettev&otilde;tja, tema esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja on saanud k&auml;tte kokkuv&otilde;tte &uuml;he eksemplari. </eesti>
<inglise>10) a notation indicating that the undertaking under inspection or the representative or employee thereof has received one copy of the summary. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i tema esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja takistab kontrollimisalast tegevust, tehakse kokkuv&otilde;ttesse sellekohane kanne, m&auml;rkides v&otilde;imaluse korral takistamise motiivid. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If an undertaking or the representative or employee thereof interferes with an inspection, a corresponding entry shall be made in the summary indicating the reasons for such interference, if possible. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) Kokkuv&otilde;te koostatakse kahes eksemplaris, millele kirjutavad alla koostaja ja kontrollitava ettev&otilde;tja esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) A summary shall be prepared in two copies which shall be signed by the person preparing the summary and the representative or employee of the undertaking under inspection. </inglise>
<eesti>Allkiri antakse igale lehek&uuml;ljele ning kontrollitav ettev&otilde;tja ja Konkurentsiamet saavad kokkuv&otilde;ttest kumbki &uuml;he eksemplari. </eesti>
<inglise>Each page of the summary shall be signed and the undertaking under inspection and the Competition Board shall each receive one copy of the summary. </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti eksemplarile lisatakse k&otilde;ik kontrollimise k&auml;igus saadud materjalid. </eesti>
<inglise>All materials obtained in the course of the inspection shall be annexed to the copy held by the Competition Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Kui kontrollitav ettev&otilde;tja, tema esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja keeldub kokkuv&otilde;ttele alla kirjutamast, tehakse kokkuv&otilde;ttesse vastav kanne ja m&auml;rgitakse allakirjutamisest keeldumise motiivid. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) If an undertaking under inspection or the representative or employee thereof refuses to sign a summary, a corresponding entry shall be made in the summary indicating the reasons for such refusal. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 61. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 61. </inglise>
<eesti>Soovituste andmine ja menetluse piiritlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Making of recommendations and limits of proceedings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib anda riigiasutusele ja kohaliku omavalituse &uuml;ksusele, f&uuml;&uuml;silisele ja juriidilisele isikule soovitusi konkurentsiolukorra parandamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may make recommendations to state agencies, local governments and natural and legal persons as to improvement of the competitive situation. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus menetluse k&auml;igus kontrollida k&otilde;igi tema j&auml;relevalve alla kuuluvate k&auml;esoleva seaduse s&auml;tete t&auml;itmist, laiendades selleks vajaduse korral menetlusosaliste ringi ja v&auml;ljudes kaebuse v&otilde;i avalduse (edaspidi kaebuse) alusel v&otilde;i oma algatusel alustatud menetluse piiridest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the course of a proceeding, the Competition Board has the right to verify compliance with all the provisions of this Act which are subject to supervision by the Competition Board and, for that purpose and if necessary, extend the circle of participants in the proceedings and transcend the limits of the proceedings initiated on the basis of a complaint or petition (hereinafter complaint) or on its own initiative. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 62. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 62. </inglise>
<eesti>Ettekirjutus ja sunniraha m&auml;&auml;ramine </eesti>
<inglise>Precepts and imposition of penalty payment </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektoril v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itjal on &otilde;igus teha ettekirjutus f&uuml;&uuml;silisele v&otilde;i juriidilisele isikule, kui nimetatud isik: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy has the right to issue a precept to a natural or legal person if the person: </inglise>
<eesti>1) j&auml;ttis Konkurentsiameti kirjalikus taotluses n&otilde;utud t&auml;htajaks teabe v&otilde;i materjalid esitamata; </eesti>
<inglise>1) fails to submit information or materials within the term specified in a written request of the Competition Board; </inglise>
<eesti>2) takistas ettev&otilde;tja asukoha v&otilde;i tegutsemiskoha kontrollimist; </eesti>
<inglise>2) interferes with an inspection at the seat or place of business of the undertaking; </inglise>
<eesti>3) j&auml;ttis suulisele arutamisele, haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamisele v&otilde;i seletuste andmisele ilmumata; </eesti>
<inglise>3) fails to appear at an oral hearing, at the preparation of an administrative offence report or when requested to provide explanations; </inglise>
<eesti>4) j&otilde;ustas koondumise, mis kuulub kontrollimisele ning mille kohta ei ole k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 27 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 1 ja l&otilde;ike 2 punkti 1 alusel tehtud vastavat otsust v&otilde;i on tehtud koondumist keelav otsus &sect; 27 l&otilde;ike 2 punkti 2 alusel v&otilde;i milleks antud loa on Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja tunnistanud kehtetuks. </eesti>
<inglise>4) puts into effect a concentration which is subject to control but concerning which a decision has not been made on the basis of clause 27 (1) 1) or (2) 1) of this Act or if a decision prohibiting the concentration has been made on the basis of clause 27 (2) 2) of this Act or the permission for the concentration has been revoked by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ettekirjutusega kohustatakse tegema n&otilde;utav tegu v&otilde;i hoiduma keelatud teost. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A precept imposes an obligation to perform a required act or to refrain from a prohibited act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ettekirjutus sisaldab hoiatust, milles m&auml;&auml;ratakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A precept shall include a warning which sets out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&auml;htp&auml;ev, milleni on aega ettekirjutus t&auml;ita (kui ettekirjutus sisaldab kohustust teatud teost hoiduda, ei ole t&auml;htp&auml;eva vaja m&auml;rkida); </eesti>
<inglise>1) the due date for compliance with the precept (if the precept contains an obligation to refrain from a certain act, the due date need not be indicated); </inglise>
<eesti>2) sunniraha summa, mida rakendatakse ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the size of the penalty payment imposed upon failure to comply with the precept; </inglise>
<eesti>3) ettekirjutuse peale edasikaebamise kord ja t&auml;htaeg. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the procedure and term for appeal against the precept. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmise korral sunniraha f&uuml;&uuml;silistele isikutele kuni 50 000 krooni ja juriidilistele isikutele kuni 100 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the case of failure to comply with a precept, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may impose a penalty payment of up to 50 000 kroons on natural persons and up to 100 000 kroons on legal persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 4 s&auml;testatud sunniraha v&otilde;ib kuni ettekirjutuse t&auml;itmiseni rakendada korduvalt. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A penalty payment provided for in subsection (4) of this section may be imposed several times until the corresponding precept is complied with. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 63. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 63. </inglise>
<eesti>&Auml;risaladuse hoidmise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Obligation to maintain business secrets </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiametil ei ole &otilde;igust avaldada ettev&otilde;tja n&otilde;usolekuta tema &auml;risaladusi, sealhulgas pangasaladusi, mida ta on teada saanud oma teenistuskohustuste t&auml;itmise k&auml;igus, teisele isikule ega neid avalikustada, kui seadusega ei ole ette n&auml;htud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Unless otherwise provided by law, the Competition Board does not have the right to disclose the business secrets, including information subject to banking secrecy, of an undertaking which have become known to the Competition Board in the course of performance of its official duties to other persons nor publish them without the consent of the undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) &Auml;risaladus ei ole: &uuml;ldsusele avaldamisele kuuluv teave ning Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja tehtud otsus ja Konkurentsiameti peadirektori, tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;i Konkurentsiameti muu ametniku koostatud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokoll, millest on &auml;risaladused v&auml;lja j&auml;etud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Information subject to disclosure to the public, decisions made by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy and administrative offence reports prepared by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy or any other official of the Competition Board from which business secrets have been excluded are not deemed to be business secrets. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamisel ei tohi Konkurentsiamet ettev&otilde;tja vastu kasutada teavet, mida k&auml;esoleva seaduse kohaselt ei saa sellele ettev&otilde;tjale avaldada. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon preparation of an administrative offence report, the Competition Board shall not use any information against an undertaking which, in accordance with the provisions of this Act, may not be disclosed to the undertaking. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Konkurentsiamet j&auml;tab avaldamisele kuuluvate otsuste tekstist v&auml;lja &auml;risaladused. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Competition Board shall exclude business secrets from the texts of decisions subject to disclosure. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 64. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 64. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebus </eesti>
<inglise>Complaints </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kaebus esitatakse Konkurentsiametile kirjalikult ning selles m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Complaints shall be submitted to the Competition Board in writing and shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) adressaat, kellele kaebus esitatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the addressee of the complaint; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kaebuse esitaja nimi, alaline elu- v&otilde;i asukoht (postiaadress) ning sidevahendi number; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name, permanent residence or seat (postal address) and telecommunications numbers of the person submitting the complaint; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kaebuse esitamise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the date of submission of the complaint; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kaebuse sisu ja p&otilde;hjused, miks selle esitaja leiab, et konkurentsi on kahjustatud ning milliseid kaebuse esitaja &otilde;igusi on rikutud; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the content of the complaint, the reasons why the person submitting the complaint finds that competition has been restricted, and the rights of the person submitting the complaint which have been violated; </inglise>
<eesti>5) kaebuse esitaja selgelt v&auml;ljendatud taotlus; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the clearly expressed request of the person submitting the complaint; </inglise>
<eesti>6) kaebuse esitaja kinnitus, et ta ei ole esitanud samas asjas kaebust v&otilde;i hagi kohtusse; </eesti>
<inglise>6) confirmation from the person submitting the complaint that the person has not filed an action with a court concerning the same matter; </inglise>
<eesti>7) k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 65 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud otsuse k&auml;ttesaamise viisi valik; </eesti>
<inglise>7) the preferable manner of delivery of a decision provided for in subsection 65 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>8) muud asjaolud, mida kaebuse esitaja peab oluliseks. </eesti>
<inglise>8) other circumstances considered significant by the person submitting the complaint. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaebusele kirjutab alla selle esitaja v&otilde;i tema esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A complaint shall be signed by the person submitting the complaint or the representative thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku ja juriidiliseks isikuks mitteoleva &uuml;henduse nimel esitatud kaebusele kirjutab alla selleks volitatud isik. </eesti>
<inglise>A complaint filed on behalf of a legal person or an association which is not a legal person shall be signed by the person who has the corresponding authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebuse esitaja esindaja lisab volitust t&otilde;endava dokumendi. </eesti>
<inglise>The representative of a person submitting the complaint shall annex a document certifying his or her authority. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku seadusliku esindaja volitusi t&otilde;endab vastava registrikaardi kehtiv koopia. </eesti>
<inglise>The authority of the legal representative of a legal person shall be certified by a valid copy of the corresponding registry card. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaebusele lisatakse kaebuse esitajale k&auml;ttesaadavad t&otilde;endid. </eesti>
<inglise>Proof available to the person submitting the complaint shall be annexed to the complaint. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusega v&otilde;idakse kaebuse esitaja nimi v&otilde;i nimetus tema p&otilde;hjendatud taotluse alusel tunnistada kolmandatele isikutele avaldamisele mittekuuluvaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) On the basis of a reasoned request from a person submitting the complaint, the name of the person may, by a decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy, be declared not to be subject to disclosure to third parties. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 65. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 65. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtumi menetlemise alustamine ja alustamisest keeldumine </eesti>
<inglise>Initiation of or refusal to initiate proceedings concerning case </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja teeb 30 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul kaebuse laekumisest: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Within thirty calendar days after the receipt of a complaint, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy shall make a decision to: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juhtumi menetlemise alustamise otsuse v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>1) initiate proceedings concerning the case, or </inglise>
<eesti>2) juhtumi menetlemise alustamisest keeldumise otsuse. </eesti>
<inglise>2) refuse to initiate proceedings concerning the case. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiameti peadirektoril ja tema aset&auml;itjal on &otilde;igus lisaks k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatule teha juhtumi menetlemise alustamise otsus oma algatusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In addition to the grounds specified in subsection (1) of this section, the Director General of the Competition Board and his or her deputy have the right to make a decision to initiate proceedings concerning a case on their own initiative. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhtumi menetlemist ei alustata ja alustatud menetlus l&otilde;petatakse, kui selgub, et: </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Proceedings shall not be initiated and initiated proceedings shall be terminated if it becomes evident that: </inglise>
<eesti>1) juhtumi menetlemine ei kuulu Konkurentsiameti p&auml;devusse; </eesti>
<inglise>1) conduct of the proceedings concerning the case does not fall within the competence of the Competition Board; </inglise>
<eesti>2) puuduvad k&auml;esoleva seaduse rikkumise tunnused; </eesti>
<inglise>2) there are no indications of a violation of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) isikut on juba karistatud sama rikkumise toimepanemise eest, s&otilde;ltumata sellest, kas karistus on m&auml;&auml;ratud v&otilde;i m&otilde;istetud Eesti Vabariigis v&otilde;i m&otilde;nes teises riigis; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the person has been previously punished for the same violation, regardless of whether the punishment was imposed in the Republic of Estonia or in any other state; </inglise>
<eesti>4) sama asi on esitatud kohtu menetlusse v&otilde;i selles asjas on algatatud kriminaalasi; </eesti>
<inglise>4) an action concerning the same matter has been filed with a court or criminal proceedings have been commenced with regard to the matter; </inglise>
<eesti>5) samas asjas on olemas j&otilde;ustunud Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsus v&otilde;i kohtuotsus, mis on tehtud samade asjaolude alusel; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy concerning the same matter or a court judgment made on the basis of the same circumstances has entered into force; </inglise>
<eesti>6) f&uuml;&uuml;siline isik on surnud v&otilde;i juriidiline isik on l&otilde;ppenud, kelle suhtes peaks alustama v&otilde;i on alustatud menetlus. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the natural person or legal person concerning whom proceedings have been or are to be commenced has died or has been dissolved. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusesse juhtumi menetlemise alustamise kohta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 1 alusel m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy on the initiation of proceedings concerning a case on the basis of clause (1) 1) of this section shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) otsuse tegemise kuup&auml;ev ja otsuse number; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the date and number of the decision; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kaebuse v&otilde;i avalduse esitaja nimi v&otilde;i nimetus, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 64 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud juhul; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name of the person submitting the complaint or petition, except in the case provided for in subsection 64 (3) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) otsuse tegemise alus koos viitega k&auml;esoleva seaduse vastavale s&auml;ttele; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the grounds for making the decision together with a reference to the relevant provision of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>4) otsuse tegija nimi. </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name of the person making the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusesse juhtumi menetlemise alustamise kohta k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 2 alusel m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy on the initiation of proceedings concerning a case on the basis of subsection (2) of this section shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) otsuse tegemise kuup&auml;ev ja otsuse number; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the date and number of the decision; </inglise>
<eesti>2) otsuse tegemise alus koos viitega k&auml;esoleva seaduse vastavale s&auml;ttele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the grounds for making the decision together with a reference to the relevant provision of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) otsuse tegija nimi. </eesti>
<inglise>3) the name of the person making the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusesse juhtumi menetlemise alustamisest keeldumise kohta m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy concerning refusal to initiate proceedings with regard to a case shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) otsuse tegemise kuup&auml;ev ja otsuse number; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the date and number of the decision; </inglise>
<eesti>2) kaebuse esitaja nimi v&otilde;i nimetus, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 64 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud juhul; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name of the person submitting the complaint, except in the case provided for in subsection 64 (3) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kaebuse sisu kokkuv&otilde;te; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a summary of the content of the complaint; </inglise>
<eesti>4) otsuse tegemise alus koos viitega k&auml;esoleva seaduse vastavale s&auml;ttele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the grounds for making the decision together with a reference to the relevant provision of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) otsuse tegemise p&otilde;hjendus; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the reasons for the decision; </inglise>
<eesti>6) otsuse tegija nimi. </eesti>
<inglise>6) the name of the person making the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 66. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 66. </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlusosalised </eesti>
<inglise>Participants in proceedings </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juhtumi menetlemisel on menetlusosalised: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The participants in proceedings concerning a case are: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kaebuse esitaja; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the person submitting the complaint; </inglise>
<eesti>2) menetluse subjekt; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the subject of the proceedings; </inglise>
<eesti>3) asjast huvitatud kolmas isik. </eesti>
<inglise>3) interested third parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Menetluse subjekt on isik, kes on v&auml;idetavalt rikkunud k&auml;esolevat seadust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The subject of the proceedings is the person who is alleged to have committed a violation of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui v&auml;idetavaks seaduserikkujaks on &uuml;hendus, on sama menetluse subjektideks ka &uuml;henduse liikmed. </eesti>
<inglise>If the alleged violation has been committed by an association of persons, the members of the association are also deemed to be subjects of the same proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>Asjast huvitatud kolmas isik on isik, kelle &otilde;igusi ja kohustusi juhtum puudutab. </eesti>
<inglise>Interested third parties are persons whose rights and obligations are affected by the case. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 67. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 67. </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlusosaliste &otilde;igused juhtumi menetlemisel </eesti>
<inglise>Rights of participants in proceedings concerning case </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Menetlusosalistel v&otilde;i nende esindajatel on &otilde;igus avaldada seisukohti, esitada t&otilde;endeid ja taotlusi juhtumi kohta. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Participants in proceedings and their representatives have the right to present their opinions and submit evidence and requests concerning the case. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Menetluse subjektil on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda &uuml;hel korral juhtumi suulise arutamise l&auml;biviimist Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja poolt. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The subject of proceedings has the right to demand one oral hearing of the case to be conducted by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kaebuse esitajal on &otilde;igus taotleda menetluses oma isiku mitteavaldamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A person submitting the complaint has the right to request non-disclosure of the identity of the person in the course of the proceedings. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Menetluse subjektil, kaebuse esitajal ja nende esindajal on &otilde;igus tutvuda k&otilde;igi juhtumi kohta kogutud materjalidega p&auml;rast Konkurentsiameti poolt kogu teabe saamist, v&auml;lja arvatud teise ettev&otilde;tja &auml;risaladus ja Konkurentsiameti sisesed dokumendid ning andmed kaebuse esitanud isiku kohta, juhul kui kaebuse esitanud isiku nimi v&otilde;i nimetus on tunnistatud avaldamisele mittekuuluvaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 64 l&otilde;ike 3 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) After the Competition Board has received all the information, the subject of the proceedings, the person submitting the complaint and their representatives have the right to examine all materials collected on the case, except business secrets of other undertakings, internal documents of the Competition Board and information concerning the person submitting the complaint if the name of the person has been declared to be not subject to disclosure on the basis of clause 64 (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 68. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 68. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtumi suuline arutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Oral hearings of cases </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Vajaduse korral v&otilde;idakse l&auml;bi viia juhtumi suuline arutamine Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja poolt etten&auml;htud p&auml;eval ja kohas, millest teavitatakse arutamisele kutsutavat isikut kirjalikult mitte v&auml;hem kui 10 kalendrip&auml;eva enne arutamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If necessary, an oral hearing of a case may be held at a time and place specified by the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy, and the persons to be heard shall be notified of the hearing in writing not less than ten calendar days before the hearing. </inglise>
<eesti>Arutamisele kutsutava isiku kirjaliku p&otilde;hjendatud taotluse alusel v&otilde;ib Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja etten&auml;htud t&auml;htaega v&otilde;i kohta muuta. </eesti>
<inglise>On the basis of a reasoned written request of a person summoned to a hearing, the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may change the term or the place of the hearing. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juhtumi suulisel arutamisel v&otilde;ivad osaleda menetlusosalised, nende esindajad, Konkurentsiameti ametnikud, Konkurentsiameti esindajad ning menetlusosaliste ja Konkurentsiameti kokkuleppel kutsutud isikud. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The participants in the proceedings, their representatives, officials of the Competition Board, representatives of the Competition Board and persons summoned on the agreement of the participants in the proceedings and the Competition Board may participate in an oral hearing of a case. </inglise>
<eesti>Suuline arutamine v&otilde;ib toimuda erinevatele menetlusosalistele erinevas kohas ja erineval ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>Oral hearings of different participants in the proceedings may be held in different places and at different times. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkurentsiametil on &otilde;igus suuline arutamine heli- v&otilde;i videosalvestada, millest suulisel arutamisel osalevaid isikuid eelnevalt teavitatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Competition Board has the right to make sound or video recordings of an oral hearing, in which case the persons participating in the hearing shall be given prior notice thereof. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Juhtumi suulise arutamise kohta koostatakse kokkuv&otilde;te, kuhu m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A summary shall be prepared concerning an oral hearing of a case and the summary shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kokkuv&otilde;tte koostamise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the time and place of preparation of the summary; </inglise>
<eesti>2) suulisel arutamisel osaleva isiku nimi ja ametikoht, juriidilise isiku puhul juriidilise isiku nimetus ja juriidilise isiku esindaja v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;taja nimi ja ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and position of the persons participating in the oral hearing or, in the case of a legal person, the name of the legal person and the name and position of the representative or employee of the legal person; </inglise>
<eesti>3) suulise arutamise k&auml;ik ja arutamisele kutsutud isikute seletused; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a description of the course of the oral hearing and the explanations of the person summoned to the hearing; </inglise>
<eesti>4) m&auml;rge t&otilde;lgi osav&otilde;tu kohta, kui t&otilde;lk osaleb; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a notation concerning the participation of an interpreter or translator if one is involved; </inglise>
<eesti>5) m&auml;rge suulise arutamise heli- v&otilde;i videosalvestamise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a notation concerning the making of sound or video recordings of the hearing; </inglise>
<eesti>6) suulise arutamise osaliste m&auml;rkused v&otilde;i nende puudumine kokkuv&otilde;tte, samuti heli- v&otilde;i videosalvestuse kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the notes or absence of notes made by participants in the oral hearing concerning the summary or the sound or video recordings; </inglise>
<eesti>7) suulise arutamise k&auml;igus Konkurentsiametile &uuml;leantud materjalide loetelu. </eesti>
<inglise>7) a list of the materials transferred to the Competition Board in the course of the oral hearing. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kokkuv&otilde;te koostatakse &uuml;hes eksemplaris ja sellele kirjutavad alla suulisel arutelul osalenud Konkurentsiameti ametnikud, kusjuures k&otilde;ik suulisel arutamisel osalenud isikud v&otilde;ivad soovi korral saada nimetatud kokkuv&otilde;tte &auml;rakirja. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A summary shall be prepared in one copy and signed by the officials of the Competition Board who participated in the hearing, but all persons who participated in the hearing have the right to receive a copy of the summary at their request. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 69. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 69. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtumi menetlemise peatamine </eesti>
<inglise>Suspension of proceedings concerning case </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib juhtumi menetlemise oma otsusega peatada, kui juhtumi kohta seisukoha v&otilde;tmisel: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may, by a decision, suspend the proceedings concerning a case if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) omab olulist t&auml;htsust antud juhtumiga seotud lahend haldus-, haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise, tsiviil- v&otilde;i kriminaalasjas, milles menetlus on pooleli; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a decision to be made in a pending administrative, administrative offence, civil or criminal matter is essential for the resolution of the case; </inglise>
<eesti>2) olulist t&auml;htsust omava t&otilde;endi saamine on takistatud, kusjuures muud vajalikud toimingud on teostatud. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the obtaining of evidence essential to the resolution of the case is hindered and all other necessary acts have been performed. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib juhtumi menetlemise oma otsusega uuendada: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may, by a decision, resume the proceedings concerning a case: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 1 m&auml;rgitud kohtu- v&otilde;i halduslahendi j&otilde;ustumisel, </eesti>
<inglise>1) upon the entry into force of a court or administrative decision specified in clause (1) 1) of this section, </inglise>
<eesti>2) k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 1 punktis 2 m&auml;rgitud t&otilde;endi saamist takistava asjaolu &auml;ralangemisel v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>2) if the circumstances hindering the evidence specified in clause (1) 2) of this section from being obtained cease to exist, or </inglise>
<eesti>3) kui selgub, et asjaolu, mille esinemist v&otilde;i mitteesinemist sooviti antud t&otilde;endiga t&otilde;endada, on v&otilde;imalik muul viisil kindlaks teha v&otilde;i sel asjaolul ei ole olulist t&auml;htsust. </eesti>
<inglise>3) if it becomes evident that the circumstances, the occurrence or absence of which was to be established by the given evidence, can be ascertained in another manner or that such circumstances are irrelevant. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 70. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 70. </inglise>
<eesti>Juhtumi menetlemise l&otilde;petamine </eesti>
<inglise>Termination of proceedings concerning case </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Enne juhtumi menetlemise l&otilde;petamist saadetakse menetluse subjektile kirjalik teade, millega antakse talle t&auml;htaeg mitte v&auml;hem kui 10 kalendrip&auml;eva, mille jooksul isikut kutsutakse tutvuma k&otilde;igi menetluse k&auml;igus kogutud materjalidega, v&auml;lja arvatud teise isiku &auml;risaladus, Konkurentsiameti sisesed dokumendid ja kaebuse esitanud isiku nimi v&otilde;i nimetus, kui see on tunnistatud avaldamisele mittekuuluvaks k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 64 l&otilde;ike 3 alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Before termination of the proceedings concerning a case, a written notice shall be sent to the subject of the proceedings by which the subject is granted a term of not less than ten calendar days to examine all the materials collected in the course of the proceedings, except business secrets of other undertakings, internal documents of the Competition Board and the name of the person submitting the complaint if the name has been declared to be not subject to disclosure on the basis of subsection 64 (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Isikul on &otilde;igus esitada t&auml;iendavat teavet 20 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud teate Konkurentsiameti poolt v&auml;ljastamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A person has the right to submit additional information within twenty calendar days after the Competition Board dispatches the notice specified in subsection (1) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>S&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumisega loetakse kogu teave esitatuks. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the expiry of this term, the submission of information shall be deemed to have been completed. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhtumi menetlemine l&otilde;petatakse kolme kuu jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja m&ouml;&ouml;dumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Proceedings concerning a case shall be terminated within three months after the expiry of the term provided for in subsection (2) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Juhtumi menetlemine l&otilde;petatakse haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamisega, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 5 ja 6 s&auml;testatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Except in the cases provided for in subsections (5) and (6) of this section, proceedings concerning a case shall be terminated by the preparation of an administrative offence report. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Juhtumi menetlemine v&otilde;idakse l&otilde;petada Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsusega juhtumi menetlemise l&otilde;petamise kohta juhul, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Proceedings concerning a case may be terminated by a corresponding decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) menetluse subjekt on riigiasutus v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksus v&otilde;i Eesti Pank, </eesti>
<inglise>1) the subject of the proceedings is a state agency, local government or the Bank of Estonia, </inglise>
<eesti>2) esinevad k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 65 l&otilde;ikes 3 s&auml;testatud asjaolud, </eesti>
<inglise>2) circumstances provided for in subsection 65 (3) of this Act become evident, </inglise>
<eesti>3) menetluse subjekt on olukorda kaubaturul oluliselt parandanud, </eesti>
<inglise>3) the subject of the proceedings has significantly improved the situation in the goods market, </inglise>
<eesti>4) konkurentsi ei ole oluliselt kahjustatud v&otilde;i </eesti>
<inglise>4) competition has not been significantly restricted, or </inglise>
<eesti>5) kaebuse esitaja on esitatust loobunud ning loobumine ei kahjusta kolmandate isikute &otilde;igusi ja vabadusi. </eesti>
<inglise>5) the person submitting the complaint has withdrawn the complaint and the withdrawal does not infringe the rights or freedoms of third parties. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli ei koostata isiku suhtes, kes andis esimesena teada k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 4 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud kokkuleppest, tegevusest v&otilde;i otsusest juhul, kui see isik ei olnud ise nimetatud kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse algataja ja kui ta on teinud t&auml;ielikku koost&ouml;&ouml;d Konkurentsiametiga juhtumi menetlemisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) An administrative offence report shall not be prepared with regard to the person who was the first to give notice of an agreement, practice or decision specified in subsection 4 (1) of this Act if the agreement, practice or decision was not initiated by the person and the person has fully co-operated with the Competition Board in the proceedings concerning the case. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 5 s&auml;testatud otsuses m&auml;rgitakse: </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A decision provided for in subsection (5) of this section shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) otsuse koostamise kuup&auml;ev; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the date of the decision; </inglise>
<eesti>2) viide menetlemise alustamise otsusele; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a reference to the decision concerning initiation of the proceedings; </inglise>
<eesti>3) andmed menetlemise subjekti kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>3) information concerning the subject of the proceedings; </inglise>
<eesti>4) menetlemise l&otilde;petamise p&otilde;hjendus ja viide k&auml;esoleva seaduse vastavale s&auml;ttele; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a reason for the termination of the proceedings and a reference to the relevant provision of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) vajaduse korral ettepanekud ja soovitused menetlusosalisele; </eesti>
<inglise>5) proposals and recommendations to the participants in the proceedings, if necessary; </inglise>
<eesti>6) otsuse peale edasikaebamise kord; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the procedure for appealing against the decision; </inglise>
<eesti>7) otsuse tegija nimi ja ametikoht. </eesti>
<inglise>7) the name and position of the person making the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 71. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 71. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuste kehtetuks tunnistamine </eesti>
<inglise>Revocation of decisions </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti peadirektor v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja v&otilde;ib tunnistada kehtetuks oma otsuse, mille aluseks olnud &otilde;igusakt on j&otilde;ustunud kohtuotsusega t&uuml;histatud v&otilde;i &otilde;igusvastaseks tunnistatud v&otilde;i on ilmnenud uusi olulisi asjaolusid v&otilde;i otsuse aluseks olnud dokumendid v&otilde;i muud materjalid olid eba&otilde;iged, mittet&auml;ielikud v&otilde;i eksitavad ning kui uute asjaolude v&otilde;i &otilde;igete ja t&auml;ielike andmete teadmisel oleks vastu v&otilde;etud teistsugune otsus. </eesti>
<inglise>The Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy may revoke his or her decision if the decision was based on a legal act which has been repealed or declared unlawful by a court judgment which has entered into force of if new relevant circumstances have become evident or if the documents or other materials on which the decision was based were incorrect, incomplete or misleading and a different decision would have been made if the new circumstances or correct and complete information had been known or available. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 72. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 72. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuste edastamine ja avaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Communication and disclosure of decisions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 65 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2, &sect;-s 69, &sect; 70 l&otilde;ikes 5 ja &sect;-s 71 s&auml;testatud otsused antakse menetluse subjektile ja kaebuse esitajale v&otilde;i nende esindajale k&auml;tte allkirja vastu v&otilde;i saadetakse posti teel v&auml;ljastusteatega. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Decisions provided for in subsections 65 (1) and (2), &sect; 69, subsection 70 (5) and &sect; 71 of this Act shall be served on the subject of the proceedings or the person submitting the complaint or their representatives against a signature or sent by post with advice of delivery. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 70 l&otilde;ikes 5 ja &sect;-s 71 s&auml;testatud otsuste kohta avaldab Konkurentsiamet teadaande v&auml;ljaandes Ametlikud Teadaanded. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Competition Board shall publish a notice concerning a decision provided for in subsection 70 (5) or &sect; 71 of this Act in the official publication Ametlikud Teadaanded. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 73. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 73. </inglise>
<eesti>Otsuste vaidlustamine </eesti>
<inglise>Appeals against decisions </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsiameti peadirektori v&otilde;i tema aset&auml;itja otsuste peale on isikul &otilde;igus kaevata halduskohtumenetluse seadustikus (RT I 1999, 31, 425; 33, &otilde;iend; 40, &otilde;iend; 96, 846; 2000, 51, 321) s&auml;testatud korras kohtusse. </eesti>
<inglise>A person has the right to file an appeal with a court against a decision of the Director General of the Competition Board or his or her deputy pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Code of Administrative Court Procedure (RT I 1999, 31, 425; 33, correction notice; 40, correction notice; 96, 846; 2000, 51, 321). </inglise>
<eesti>9. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 9 </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 74. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 74. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutuse kohaldamine </eesti>
<inglise>Application of liability </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Juriidilisele isikule karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramisel k&auml;esoleva seaduse v&otilde;i selle alusel kehtestatud &otilde;igusaktide rikkumise eest arvestatakse &otilde;iguserikkumise raskust, laadi ja teisi asjaolusid, rikkuja koost&ouml;&ouml;valmidust Konkurentsiametiga ning keelatud tegevuse l&otilde;petamist enne karistuse m&auml;&auml;ramist. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Upon the imposition of a punishment on a legal person for violation of this Act or legislation established on the basis thereof, the gravity, nature and other circumstances of the violation, the extent to which the offender co-operates with the Competition Board and any termination of the prohibited activity before the imposition of the punishment shall be taken into consideration. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juriidilisele isikule ei kohaldata karistust, kui &otilde;iguserikkumise toimepanemisest v&otilde;i lepingu t&auml;itmise l&otilde;petamisest v&otilde;i kehtetuks muutumisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud rohkem kui kolm aastat. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A punishment shall not be imposed on a legal person if more than three years have passed since the commission of the violation, the termination of performance of an agreement or the expiry of the term of validity of the agreement. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 75. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 75. </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku vastutus haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability of legal person for administrative offence </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rahandusministrile eba&otilde;ige, mittet&auml;ieliku v&otilde;i eksitava teabe esitamise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 500 kuni 50 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A fine of 500 to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed for submission of incorrect, incomplete or misleading information to the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Riigiabi v&auml;&auml;rkasutamise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv 500 kuni 50 000 krooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) A fine of 500 to 50 000 kroons shall be imposed for misuse of state aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Konkurentsiametile eba&otilde;ige, mittet&auml;ieliku v&otilde;i eksitava teabe esitamise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 1 protsent seaduserikkuja trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele eelnenud majandusaasta k&auml;ibest. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) A fine in the amount of up to 1 per cent of the turnover of the offender during the financial year preceding the decision to impose the fine shall be imposed for submission of incorrect, incomplete or misleading information to the Competition Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Turguvalitseva seisundi kuritarvitamise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 10 protsenti seaduserikkuja trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele eelnenud majandusaasta k&auml;ibest. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A fine in the amount of up to 10 per cent of the turnover of the offender during the financial year preceding the decision to impose the fine shall be imposed for abuse of a dominant position. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Konkurentsi kahjustava kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse keelu rikkumise eest, samuti erandit vajava kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse eest ilma erandi loata v&otilde;i erandi loa tingimuste rikkumise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 10 protsenti seaduserikkuja trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele eelnenud majandusaasta k&auml;ibest. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A fine in the amount of up to 10 per cent of the turnover of the offender during the financial year preceding the decision to impose the fine shall be imposed for violation of a prohibition on an agreement, practice or decision restricting competition, for entry into an agreement, engagement in a practice or the making of a decision requiring an exemption without obtaining such exemption, and for violation of the conditions of an exemption. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Koondumisest t&auml;htaegselt teatamata j&auml;tmise, samuti koondumise keelu v&otilde;i koondumise loa tingimuste rikkumise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 10 protsenti seaduserikkuja trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele eelnenud majandusaasta k&auml;ibest. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A fine in the amount of up to 10 per cent of the turnover of the offender during the financial year preceding the decision to impose the fine shall be imposed for failure to give notice of a concentration within the specified term and for violation of a prohibition on concentration or the conditions of permission to concentrate. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omava juriidilise isiku raamatupidamises erinevate p&otilde;hi- ja lisategevusalade vahel selge vahe mittehoidmise eest - m&auml;&auml;ratakse rahatrahv kuni 1 protsent seaduserikkuja trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele eelnenud majandusaasta k&auml;ibest. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) A fine in the amount of up to 1 per cent of the turnover of the offender during the financial year preceding the decision to impose the fine shall be imposed on a legal person with special or exclusive rights or in control of essential facilities which fails to draw a clear distinction between primary and secondary activities in its accounts. </inglise>
<eesti>(8) K&auml;ive k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi t&auml;henduses on ettev&otilde;tja realiseerimise netok&auml;ive v&otilde;i krediidi- v&otilde;i finantseerimisasutuse k&auml;ive, mis on arvutatud vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 23 l&otilde;ikele 2, v&otilde;i kindlustusandja k&auml;ive, mis on arvutatud vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 23 l&otilde;ikele 3, v&otilde;i nende n&auml;itajate puudumise korral juriidilise isiku tulud, millest on maha arvatud k&auml;ibemaks ja tulumaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) For the purposes of this section, turnover is the net realised turnover of an undertaking or the turnover of a credit or financial institution calculated pursuant to subsection 23 (2) of this Act, or the turnover of an insurer calculated pursuant to subsection 23 (3) of this Act, or, in the absence of such indicators, the income of the legal person after the deduction of value added tax and income tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Kui seaduserikkujal ei olnud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 8 nimetatud k&auml;ivet trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise otsusele eelnenud majandusaastal, on tema k&auml;ibeks trahvi m&auml;&auml;ramise aasta tegelik k&auml;ive kuni haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamiseni. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) If an offender did not effect any turnover specified in subsection (8) of this section during the financial year preceding the decision to impose a fine, the actual turnover effected by the person during the year in which the fine is imposed and until the administrative offence report is prepared shall be considered as the turnover of the offender. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 76. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 76. </inglise>
<eesti>Haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamine </eesti>
<inglise>Preparation of administrative offence reports </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ettev&otilde;tja kutsutakse haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise protokolli koostamisele kirjaliku kutsega vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 58. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An undertaking shall be summoned to the preparation of an administrative offence report by a written summons pursuant to &sect; 58 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kutses m&auml;rgitakse, millise haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise eest protokoll koostatakse. </eesti>
<inglise>The summons shall set out the administrative offence concerning which the report is to be prepared. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 75 l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste kohta protokolli koostamise &otilde;igus on rahandusministri volitatud ametnikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Officials authorised by the Minister of Finance have the right to prepare reports concerning the administrative offences provided for in subsection 75 (1) and (2) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 75 l&otilde;igetes 3-7 s&auml;testatud haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste kohta protokolli koostamise &otilde;igus on Konkurentsiameti peadirektoril ja tema aset&auml;itjal ning nende volitatud Konkurentsiameti ametnikul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The Director General of the Competition Board and his or her deputy and officials of the Competition Board authorised by the Director General or his or her deputy have the right to prepare reports concerning the administrative offences provided for in subsections 75 (3) -(7) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 2 ja 3 nimetatud protokoll sisaldab j&auml;rgmisi andmeid: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) A report specified in subsection (2) or (3) of this section shall set out: </inglise>
<eesti>1) koostamise aeg ja koht; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the time and place of preparation; </inglise>
<eesti>2) asutuse nimetus, kelle esindaja koostab protokolli, ja aadress; </eesti>
<inglise>2) the name and address of the agency the representative of which prepared the report; </inglise>
<eesti>3) protokolli koostanud isiku ametinimetus, ees- ja perekonnanimi; </eesti>
<inglise>3) the official title, given name and surname of the person who prepared the report; </inglise>
<eesti>4) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja nimetus v&otilde;i &auml;rinimi, registreerimise number ja asukoht; </eesti>
<inglise>4) the name or business name, registration number and seat of the administrative offender; </inglise>
<eesti>5) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja ees- ja perekonnanimi ning ametikoht; </eesti>
<inglise>5) the given name, surname and position of the representative of the administrative offender; </inglise>
<eesti>6) haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise koht, aeg ja kirjeldus; </eesti>
<inglise>6) the place, time and description of the administrative offence; </inglise>
<eesti>7) viide k&auml;esoleva seaduse s&auml;ttele, mille alusel haldusvastutust kohaldatakse; </eesti>
<inglise>7) a reference to the provisions of this Act which are the basis for imposition of administrative liability; </inglise>
<eesti>8) haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindaja seletus v&otilde;i m&auml;rge seletuse andmisest loobumise kohta; </eesti>
<inglise>8) an explanation provided by the representative of the administrative offender or a notation concerning refusal to provide an explanation; </inglise>
<eesti>9) m&auml;rge selle kohta, et haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja esindajale on tutvustatud tema &otilde;igust kasutada &otilde;igusabi. </eesti>
<inglise>9) a notation indicating that the representative of the administrative offender has been informed of his or her right to obtain legal aid. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Protokollile kirjutavad alla selle koostanud isik ja haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja v&otilde;i tema esindaja. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The person who prepares a report and the administrative offender or his or her representative shall sign the report. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja v&otilde;i tema esindaja keeldub protokollile alla kirjutamast, tehakse sellesse vastav kanne. </eesti>
<inglise>If the administrative offender or his or her representative refuses to sign the report, a corresponding entry shall be made therein. </inglise>
<eesti>Protokollile lisatakse haldus&otilde;iguserikkuja v&otilde;i tema esindaja kirjalikud m&auml;rkused protokolli, samuti protokollile allakirjutamisest keeldumise kohta ning allakirjutamisest keeldumise motiivid. </eesti>
<inglise>Written notes made by the administrative offender or his or her representative concerning the report or his or her refusal to sign the report, and the reasons for such refusal shall be annexed to the report. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) Protokoll esitatakse kohtule arutamiseks 10 kalendrip&auml;eva jooksul selle koostamisest arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) A report shall be submitted for hearing by a court within ten calendar days as of the preparation of the report. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 77. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 77. </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlus haldus&otilde;iguserikkumise asjas </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings in matters concerning administrative offences </inglise>
<eesti>Menetlus k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud juriidilise isiku &otilde;iguserikkumise asjas toimub k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud korras ja k&auml;esolevas seaduses otseselt reguleerimata juhtudel haldus&otilde;iguserikkumiste seadustikus (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 45, &otilde;iend; 58, 608; 60, 616; 87, 792; 92, 825; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301 ja 305; 51, 321; 54, 346, 348 ja 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544 ja 548; 89, 578; 95, 609 ja 613; 2001, 3, 5; 17, 76; 18, 87; 21, 115 ja 116; 31, 174; 42, 236) ja t&auml;itemenetluse seadustikus (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings in matters concerning administrative offences by legal persons provided for in this Act shall be conducted pursuant to the procedure provided by this Act and, in cases not directly regulated by this Act, pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Code of Administrative Offences (RT 1992, 29, 396; RT I 1999, 41, 496; 45, correction notice; 58, 608; 60, 616; 87, 792; 92, 825; 95, 843; 2000, 10, 58; 25, 141; 28, 167; 29, 169; 40, 247; 49, 301 and 305; 51, 321; 54, 346, 348 and 351; 55, 361; 58, 376; 84, 533; 86, 544 and 548; 89, 578; 95, 609 and 613; 2001, 3, 5; 17, 76; 18, 87; 21, 115 and 116; 31, 174; 42, 236) and the Code of Enforcement Procedure (RT I 1993, 49, 693; 2001, 29, 156; 43, 238). </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 78. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 78. </inglise>
<eesti>Kahjude h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for damage </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;esoleva seadusega keelatud tegude toimepanemisega tekitatud varaline v&otilde;i muu kahju kuulub h&uuml;vitamisele tsiviilkorras. </eesti>
<inglise>Proprietary or other damage caused by acts prohibited by this Act shall be subject to compensation by way of civil procedure. </inglise>
<eesti>10. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 10 </inglise>
<eesti>Rakenduss&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Implementing Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 79. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 79. </inglise>
<eesti>Kriminaalkoodeksi t&auml;iendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Amendment of Criminal Code </inglise>
<eesti>Kriminaalkoodeksit (RT 1992, 20, 288; RT I 1999, 38, 485; 57, 595, 597 ja 598; 60, 616; 97, 859; 102, 907; 2000, 10, 55; 28, 167; 29, 173; 33, 193; 40, 247; 49, 301 ja 305; 54, 351; 57, 373; 58, 376; 84, 533; 92, 597; 104, 685; 2001, 21, 115 ja 116; 31, 174) t&auml;iendatakse &sect;-dega 148 (16) -148 (19) j&auml;rgmises s&otilde;nastuses: </eesti>
<inglise>Sections 148 (16) -148 (19) are added to the Criminal Code (RT 1992, 20, 288; RT I 1999, 38, 485; 57, 595, 597 and 598; 60, 616; 97, 859; 102, 907; 2000, 10, 55; 28, 167; 29, 173; 33, 193; 40, 247; 49, 301 and 305; 54, 351; 57, 373; 58, 376; 84, 533; 92, 597; 104, 685; 2001, 21, 115 and 116; 31, 174) in the following wording: </inglise>
<eesti>"&sect; 148 (16). </eesti>
<inglise>"&sect; 148 (16). </inglise>
<eesti>Turguvalitseva seisundi kuritarvitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Abuse of dominant position </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku juhatuse, seda asendava organi v&otilde;i n&otilde;ukogu liikme poolt eba&otilde;iglaste &auml;ritingimuste kehtestamise v&otilde;i ostjate kahjuks tootmise, teenindamise, kaubaturu, tehnilise arengu v&otilde;i investeerimise piiramise v&otilde;i muu turguvalitseva seisundi otsest v&otilde;i kaudset kuritarvitamist kaubaturul p&otilde;hjustava tegevuse eest - karistatakse rahatrahvi v&otilde;i vabadusekaotusega kuni kolme aastani. </eesti>
<inglise>A member of the management board, of a body substituting for the management board or of the supervisory board of a legal person who establishes unfair trading conditions, limits production, services, the market, technical development or investment to the prejudice of consumers or who engages in other activities causing a direct or indirect abuse of a dominant position shall be punished by a fine or up to three years' imprisonment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 148 (17). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 148 (17). </inglise>
<eesti>Konkurentsi kahjustav kokkulepe, tegevus v&otilde;i otsus </eesti>
<inglise>Agreements, practices or decisions restricting competition </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku juhatuse, seda asendava organi v&otilde;i n&otilde;ukogu liikme poolt konkurentsi kahjustava kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse keelu rikkumise eest, samuti erandit vajava kokkuleppe, tegevuse v&otilde;i otsuse eest ilma erandi loata v&otilde;i erandi loa tingimuste rikkumise eest - karistatakse rahatrahvi v&otilde;i vabadusekaotusega kuni kolme aastani. </eesti>
<inglise>A member of the management board, of a body substituting for the management board or of the supervisory board of a legal person who violates a prohibition on an agreement, practice or decision restricting competition or who enters into an agreement, engages in practices or makes a decision requiring an exemption without obtaining such exemption or who violates the conditions of an exemption shall be punished by a fine or up to three years' imprisonment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 148 (18). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 148 (18). </inglise>
<eesti>Koondumisega seotud kohustuste t&auml;itmata j&auml;tmine </eesti>
<inglise>Failure to perform obligations relating to concentration </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku juhatuse, seda asendava organi v&otilde;i n&otilde;ukogu liikme poolt koondumisest t&auml;htaegselt teatamata j&auml;tmise, samuti koondumise keelu v&otilde;i koondumise loa tingimuste rikkumise eest - karistatakse rahatrahvi v&otilde;i vabadusekaotusega kuni kolme aastani. </eesti>
<inglise>A member of the management board, of a body substituting for the management board or of a supervisory board of a legal person who fails to give notice of a concentration within the specified term or who violates a prohibition on concentration or the conditions of permission to concentrate shall be punished by a fine or up to three years' imprisonment. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 148 (19). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 148 (19). </inglise>
<eesti>Eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omava juriidilise isiku poolt raamatupidamises selge vahe mittehoidmine </eesti>
<inglise>Failure to draw clear distinction between primary and secondary activities in accounts of legal person with special or exclusive rights or in control of essential facilities </inglise>
<eesti>Juriidilise isiku juhatuse, seda asendava organi v&otilde;i n&otilde;ukogu liikme poolt eri- v&otilde;i ainu&otilde;igust v&otilde;i olulist vahendit omava juriidilise isiku raamatupidamises erinevate p&otilde;hi- ja lisategevusalade vahel selge vahe mittehoidmist p&otilde;hjustava tegevuse eest - karistatakse rahatrahvi v&otilde;i vabadusekaotusega kuni kolme aastani." </eesti>
<inglise>A member of the management board, of a body substituting for the management board or of a supervisory board of a legal person with special or exclusive rights or in control of essential facilities who engages in activities resulting in failure to draw a clear distinction between primary and secondary activities in the accounts of the legal person shall be punished by a fine or up to three years' imprisonment." </inglise>
