<eesti>Seaduse rakendamine </eesti>
<inglise>Implementation of Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolevat seadust kohaldatakse k&otilde;igi konkurentsi kahjustavate kokkulepete, koosk&otilde;lastatud tegevuste ja otsuste suhtes, mis kehtivad k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumise hetkel ja mis teostatakse p&auml;rast seda. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act applies to all agreements, concerted practices and decisions which restrict competition and are in force at the moment of the entry into force of this Act and which are carried out thereafter. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Juhtumeid, mille menetlemine on alustatud enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist, menetletakse juhtumi menetluse alustamise ajal kehtinud seaduse j&auml;rgi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Proceedings initiated before the entry into force of this Act shall be conducted pursuant to the Act in force at the time of initiation of the proceedings concerning the case. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Eri- ja ainu&otilde;iguseks loetakse ka enne 1998. aasta 1. oktoobrit ettev&otilde;tjale riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;ksuse poolt &uuml;ksk&otilde;ik millises vormis ja korras antud luba, mis v&otilde;imaldab ettev&otilde;tjal olla kaubaturul teiste ettev&otilde;tjatega v&otilde;rreldes eelisseisundis v&otilde;i ainsaks ettev&otilde;tjaks antud kaubaturul. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Permission granted in any form or pursuant to any procedure to an undertaking by the state or a local government before 1 October 1998 which enables the undertaking to have a competitive advantage over other undertakings in a goods market or to be the only undertaking in the market shall also be deemed to be a special or exclusive right. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vabariigi Valitsus ja ministrid viivad konkurentsiseaduse (RT I 1998, 30, 410; 1999, 89, 813; 2000, 53, 343; RT III 2000, 21, 232) alusel vastuv&otilde;etud m&auml;&auml;rused k&auml;esoleva seadusega koosk&otilde;lla kolme kuu jooksul p&auml;rast k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Government of the Republic and its ministers shall bring the regulations passed on the basis of the Competition Act (RT I 1998, 30, 410; 1999, 89, 813; 2000, 53, 343; RT III 2000, 21, 232) into conformity with this Act within three months after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 88. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 88. </inglise>
<eesti>Olemasoleva riigiabi menetlemine </eesti>
<inglise>Proceedings concerning existing state aid </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Olemasolev riigiabi on abiprogrammid ja individuaalne riigiabi, mida hakati andma p&auml;rast 1995. aasta 1. jaanuari ja enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumist ning mida antakse j&auml;tkuvalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse kehtimise ajal, samuti riigiabi, mille andmiseks rahandusminister v&otilde;i Vabariigi Valitsus on andnud loa, ning riigiabi, mida loetakse lubatuks vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 36 l&otilde;ikele 3. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Existing state aid is taken to mean aid schemes and individual state aid the grant of which commenced between 1 January 1995 and the entry into force of this Act and continued after the entry into force of this Act, state aid for the grant of which permission has been granted by the Minister of Finance or the Government of the Republic, and state aid which is deemed to be permitted pursuant to subsection 36 (3) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Olemasolevat riigiabi hinnatakse vastavalt k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud &uuml;ldtingimustele ja k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 31 l&otilde;ike 6 alusel kehtestatud eritingimustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Existing state aid shall be assessed in accordance with the general requirements provided for in this Act and pursuant to the special requirements established on the basis of subsection 31 (6) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui rahandusminister leiab, et olemasolev riigiabi ei sobi v&otilde;i enam ei sobi kokku &uuml;ldiste huvidega, teatab ta kirjalikult riigiabi andjale oma esialgsest seisukohast ja annab talle v&otilde;imaluse esitada &uuml;he kuu jooksul omapoolseid selgitusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If the Minister of Finance finds that existing state aid is not or is no longer compatible with the public interest, he or she shall notify the grantor of the state aid in writing of his or her preliminary view and give the grantor the opportunity to submit its comments within one month. </inglise>
<eesti>P&otilde;hjendatud juhtudel v&otilde;ib rahandusminister seda t&auml;htaega pikendada. </eesti>
<inglise>In duly justified cases, the Minister of Finance may extend the term. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Kui rahandusminister teeb riigiabi andja poolt vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikele 3 esitatud selgituste p&otilde;hjal otsuse, et olemasolev riigiabi on kokkusobiv &uuml;ldiste huvidega, teatab ta sellest riigiabi andjale. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) If the Minister of Finance, on the basis of the comments submitted by a grantor of state aid pursuant to subsection (3) of this section, makes a decision that the existing state aid is compatible with the public interest, the Minister of Finance shall notify the grantor of state aid of the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui rahandusminister teeb riigiabi andja poolt vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikele 3 esitatud selgituste p&otilde;hjal otsuse, et olemasolev riigiabi ei sobi kokku &uuml;ldiste huvidega, on rahandusministril &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda riigiabi sisulist muutmist ja m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks uue loa taotluse esitamist v&otilde;i m&auml;&auml;ratud t&auml;htajaks riigiabi andmise l&otilde;petamist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the Minister of Finance, on the basis of the comments submitted by a grantor of state aid pursuant to subsection (3) of this section, makes a decision that the existing state aid is not compatible with the public interest, the Minister of Finance has the right to request substantive amendment of the aid scheme and submission of a new application for permission within a specified term or termination of the grant of the state aid within a specified term. </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ike 5 alusel esitatavat riigiabi andmise loa taotlust menetletakse vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 36. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) Proceedings concerning applications for permission to grant state aid submitted on the basis of subsection (5) of this section shall be conducted pursuant to &sect; 36 of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(7) Kui riigiabi andja ei t&auml;ida t&auml;htajaks rahandusministri poolt vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikele 5 esitatud n&otilde;udeid, loetakse p&auml;rast eelnimetud t&auml;htaega antavat riigiabi ebaseaduslikuks riigiabiks ning rahandusministril on &otilde;igus algatada menetlus vastavalt k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-le 42. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) If a grantor of state aid fails to comply with the requirements set by the Minister of Finance pursuant to subsection (5) of this section within the specified term, the state aid granted after the expiry of the term is deemed to be unlawful state aid and the Minister of Finance has the right to initiate proceedings pursuant to &sect; 42 of this Act. </inglise>
